ts, subways and parks. Conducted by the NYC Department of Homeless Services (DHS), HOPE is a point-in-time estimate of unsheltered indivi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; color: #141823; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, &#39;lucida grande&#39;, tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px;\"&gt;duals to project service needs, allocate resources for the street homeless population, and educate and engage New Yorkers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=\"margin: 6px 0px; color: #141823; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, &#39;lucida grande&#39;, tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px;\"&gt;Here are the details:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=\"margin: 6px 0px; color: #141823; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, &#39;lucida grande&#39;, tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px;\"&gt;When: January 26, 2015&lt;br /&gt;Where: PS 41- 116 West 11th Street (Note: this is where I signed up for but feel free to go elsewhere)&lt;br /&gt;Team Name: NYU Law SBA&lt;br /&gt;How: By clicking this link --&gt;&nbsp;&lt;a style=\"color: #3b5998; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://a071-hope.nyc.gov/hope/register.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"&gt;https://a071-hope.nyc.gov/hope/register.aspx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=\"margin: 6px 0px; color: #141823; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, &#39;lucida grande&#39;, tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px;\"&gt;If you have any questions about the event, signing up or anything else do not hesitate to contact me. After signing up, please send me an email at cjp406@nyu.edu so that I can make sure the list is accurate with DHS&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All volunteers can meet here before the event. Drink coffee before going out and receive ear warmers.&lt;/p&gt;\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\