0','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/german_orchestra.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(93,1,'2012-09-25 04:14:59','2012-09-25 04:14:59','','LocalEastVillageSightingsSchoolapa2012','','inherit','open','open','','localeastvillagesightingsschoolapa2012','','','2012-09-25 04:14:59','2012-09-25 04:14:59','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/LocalEastVillageSightingsSchoolapa2012.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(95,1,'2012-09-25 04:15:04','2012-09-25 04:15:04','','marcelvandam+frankie2012','','inherit','open','open','','marcelvandamfrankie2012','','','2012-09-25 04:15:04','2012-09-25 04:15:04','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/marcelvandam+frankie2012.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(96,1,'2012-09-25 04:15:06','2012-09-25 04:15:06','','Maria_Schoolbook2011','','inherit','open','open','','maria_schoolbook2011','','','2012-09-25 04:15:06','2012-09-25 04:15:06','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Maria_Schoolbook2011.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(97,1,'2012-09-25 04:15:10','2012-09-25 04:15:10','','maria','','inherit','open','open','','maria','','','2012-09-25 04:15:10','2012-09-25 04:15:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/maria.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(98,1,'2012-09-25 04:15:18','2012-09-25 04:15:18','','originalworks_icon','','inherit','open','open','','originalworks_icon','','','2012-09-25 04:15:18','2012-09-25 04:15:18','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/originalworks_icon.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(118,1,'2012-09-25 04:51:40','2012-09-25 04:51:40','','children','','inherit','open','open','','children','','','2012-09-25 04:51:40','2012-09-25 04:51:40','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/children.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(126,1,'2012-09-25 05:08:19','2012-09-25 05:08:19','','LocalEastVillageSightingsSchoolapa2012','','inherit','open','open','','localeastvillagesightingsschoolapa2012-2','','','2015-02-09 02:30:23','2015-02-09 07:30:23','',123,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/LocalEastVillageSightingsSchoolapa20121.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(861,1,'2013-06-07 11:46:16','2013-06-07 15:46:16','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/cws-pta-bylaws-please-review-we-will-vote-on-these-bylaws-at-our-meeting-on-weds-12-june-after-drop-off-in-the-lobby/final-by-laws/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-862\">Final By-Laws</a>','CWS PTA Bylaws:  Please review--we will vote on these bylaws at our  meeting on Weds 12 June after drop-off in the lobby.','','publish','open','open','','cws-pta-bylaws-please-review-we-will-vote-on-these-bylaws-at-our-meeting-on-weds-12-june-after-drop-off-in-the-lobby','','','2013-06-07 11:46:16','2013-06-07 15:46:16','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=861',0,'post','',0),(870,1,'2013-06-07 11:57:14','2013-06-07 15:57:14','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/marias-20th-anniversary-party-2/20thanniversarymariarev-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-871\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-871\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20thanniversarymariaREV1-550x711.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"711\" /></a>','Maria\'s 20th Anniversary Party!','','publish','open','open','','marias-20th-anniversary-party-2','','','2013-06-07 11:57:14','2013-06-07 15:57:14','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=870',0,'post','',0),(874,1,'2013-06-11 10:02:41','2013-06-11 14:02:41','<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/update-for-june-2013/20thanniversarymariarev-3/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-875\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-875\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/20thanniversarymariaREV2-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Month of June 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">phone numbers:212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376</p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<strong>Thanks to all for a wonderful 19<sup>th</sup> Annual Arts and Science Fair</strong>—Judy and Elizabeth for chairing; Ian, Keiko, Sean, Tiffany, Steve, Paul, Holly, Mike, Sayoko, Roka, Tomo, Rosie, Margot, Patrizia, Beth, Melissa, Todd, Gilda, Amy, Francesca, Jen, Khadejah, Heather, Scott, Julie, Rina, John, Chris, Andrew, Paul; teachers Gary, Jessica, Scott, Jeff, Casey, Miriam, Beverly, Molly, Suma; our dear school secretary Joyce and principal Maria; alumni Leopold, Orion and Cyanne; School Safety Officers Baptiste and Das; our custodial staff: Manny, Alicia, and Francesca—and so many more, especially the huge face-painting crew and many kitchen helpers.\n\n<strong>Thanks to all for participating in our mini Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our beautiful library from June 1<sup>st</sup>-June 8<sup>th</sup>. </strong>We will be having a full book fair in the Fall dedicated to Carol, our recently-retired school librarian who passed away in March.\n\n<strong>Celebrate Maria’s 20<sup>th</sup> Anniversary as Co-Founder and Principal of The Children\'s Workshop School on Thursday 20 June from 4:30-6:30 at Gnocco on 10<sup>th</sup> Street between Ave A and Ave B!  $25 per person for a delicious buffet/$5 per drink—kids (under 12) are free!  The kids will sing a special song for Maria!</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>Our Chorus Club performed at Turtle Bay Music School in May</strong> and on Sunday 2 June at 7pm, Terry, our music teacher from Turtle Bay Music School sang with her quartet at The Living Room.\n\n<strong>CWS dad David Riker wrote a documentary, <em>Dirty Wars</em>,</strong> which premiered on Friday 7 June at the IFC Center and is also playing at Lincoln Center. Directed and shot by Richard Rowley, the film follows investigative journalist Jeremy Scahill into the darkest corners of American\'s Global War on Terror, from Afghanistan to Yemen and Somalia. A sensation at this year\'s Sundance Film Festival, it won the Cinematography Award for US Documentary, and took home the Grand Jury Prize at the Boston Independent Film Festival. See the film’s site:  <a href=\"http://www.dirtywars.org/\">http://www.dirtywars.org</a>\n\n<strong>Turtle Bay Music School Saturday Music Project applications</strong>—this is a tuition-free program open to CWS students who will be in 3<sup>rd</sup>, 4<sup>th</sup>, or 5<sup>th</sup> grade next year and want to begin serious study of an instrument.  For more info and application go to <a href=\"http://www.tbms.org/saturday-music-project/\">http://www.tbms.org/saturday-music-project/</a>\n\nOur fifth graders did <strong>NOT take the ELA field tests</strong>—parents said no so Maria said NO.\n\n<strong>We had a great year in the library!</strong>  Six hundred kids came through every week.  Please do a final search for any unreturned books in your home—they do show up sometimes!  Notes will go out the first week in June if your child(ren) owe any library books.\n\nLunch bills for April and May will be going out the first week in June. Please pay if you have not done so and consider estimating the cost for the month of June.\n\n<strong>Looking for parents with carpentry skills to help rebuild the outdoor classroom at Campos Garden damaged by Hurricane Sandy.</strong>  Need help in planning project, pricing materials, and construction over the summer as part of the grant received from Citizens Committee of NYC.  If interested contact Melissa at <a href=\"mailto:fundraising@childrensworkshopschool.org\">fundraising@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>.  Casey’s class has already been working in the Campos Garden and Helen’s class has been working in the children’s garden on the corner of 12<sup>th</sup> and B.\n\n<strong>Check out this NYCFoodscape Blog post about our third graders planting a Three Sisters Garden: </strong><a href=\"http://blog.nycfoodscape.com/?p=646\">http://blog.nycfoodscape.com/?p=646</a>\n\nRaffles:  Isabel won the bike!  Ziad won the American Girl doll for his sister!\n\nPaul reports:  <strong>“Congratulations to all the CWS athletes who took part in the New York Road Runners\' Jamboree at Randall\'s Island on May 5th.</strong> On the podium were four 3rd graders, a 4th grader &amp; a 5th grader:\nFederico Redondo, 3rd in the 100m\nSimon Baker, 3rd in the 200m\nMaxo Ryncavage, 2nd in the shot putt\nFederico, Simon, Maxo &amp; Seamus Lee Henry, 3rd in the 4x200m relay\nRory Power, 1st in the long jump\nAndré Hetu, 2nd in the 100m &amp; 3rd in the long jump\nRory &amp; André are with a local track team (<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=3129fd3c104f46abb6567a7f91d70160&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.fivepointsrunners.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.fivepointsrunners.com</a>) while the other four represented CWS. Well done, boys!\"\n\n<strong>The Experimental Dance Group</strong> was featured in a <em>Wall Street Journal</em> article and performed at the NYC Educators Student Dance Festival on 18 May and the Lower East Side Festival of the Arts on 25 May at the Theater for the New City--congrats to Mr. Scott and the dancers:  Kyla, Haley, Chloe, Matilda, Isabella, Simone, Franny, Olive, Victoria, Katya, Stella, Miette and Erin. <a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424127887323335404578445561193200852.html#articleTabs_comments%3D%26articleTabs%3Darticle\">http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424127887323335404578445561193200852.html#articleTabs_comments%3D%26articleTabs%3Darticle</a>\n\nRachel and her JourneyDance regulars marched in the Dance Parade! The next mother/daughter JourneyDance is Saturday 8 June.  See dancewithrachel.com for details.\n\n<strong>The fifth graders and Maria are back from their Washington DC trip!  They met with Congressman John Lewis and got a private tour of the Supreme Court.</strong>\n\n<strong><em>End of Year Thank Yous:\n</em></strong>\nThanks to <strong>the School Leadership Team</strong> for their service this year:  Judy, chair; Cassy, Nancy, and Jen, parent members; Beth and Elizabeth, PTA reps;  Maria and Dorothy, admin members; Susan, Molly, Suma and Crystal, teacher members.\n\nThanks to <strong>the Tech</strong> <strong>Team</strong>: Keiko, Ian, teachers Crystal, Jessica, Scott, and Susan—thanks to their grant-writing skills, we have smart boards and laptop carts.\n\nThanks to our <strong>Activist Committee</strong>: Hope, whose efforts got us another school safety officer, Nancy with testing awareness, Jen for starting the opting-out of InBloom info-sharing initiative.\n\nThanks to the <strong>Nutrition Committee</strong>-Leslie and Elizabeth for working with EVCS and The Spectrum School so that our cafeteria offers the healthy lunch menu and for promoting healthy snacks yet respect for all food choices.\n\nThanks to our <strong>Fundraising Committee</strong>:  Melissa, Margot, Natalie, Heather, Sayoko, Roxanne, Ken, Julie and Paul—writing and winning grants (Melissa!!), running the weekly Coffee And.. before Community Meeting\n\nThanks to those who worked on the <strong>CD of Community Meeting songs</strong>:  Gary, Elizabeth and Tiffany\n\nThanks to Nancy for being the <strong>Lice</strong> <strong>Lady</strong>—coordinating all-school lice checks—and to Judy and Rachel for helping out on the lice-check days.\n\nThanks to our wonderful longtime <strong>school safety officer</strong>, Officer Baptiste, and our new school safety officer, Officer Das. We are lucky to have you keeping our children safe!\n\nThanks to our <strong>late pass writers</strong>:  Judy, Nancy, Elizabeth and Ally.\n\nThanks to the <strong>Library Volunteers</strong>:  Holly, Margot and Jimmy for helping to maintain our beautiful library’s collection.\n\nThanks to Rosie for designing the <strong>CWS t-shirts and many event flyers</strong> and Rodrigo for designing the <strong>Schoolapalooza poster</strong>.\n\nThank you to outgoing <strong>PTA Executive Board</strong> member Julie, continuing members Beth, Elizabeth, Heidi, Tiffany and Keiko and incoming members Rina, Shavvy and Mary.\n\nThank you to Joyce, Darryl and Rachel for running our <strong>fantastic After-School Clubs</strong>—and to all the club leaders!\n\nThank you to Ed, who leads <strong>the CWS Band</strong>, Terry from <strong>Turtle Bay Music School,</strong> and our <strong>Bent on Learning</strong> yoga teachers.\n\nThanks to <strong>those who chair our many events:</strong>   Elizabeth and Julie for chairing October’s Harvest Festival; Bari for chairing the Holiday Craft Fair; Jen for coordinating Original Works; Kim, Rachel, Ian, Nancy, Cassy, Evan, Tiffany, Rina, Lori et al for chairing and running Schoolapalooza; Judy and Elizabeth for chairing the Arts and Science Fair; Melissa for coordinating the Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our lovely library; and the 4th grade families for making and serving breakfast to the 5<sup>th</sup> grade families after the Moving Up Ceremony.\n\nA very special thank you to Mo and Jean Campbell and their School Bell Foundation which helps to fund our annual <strong>fourth-grade farm trip</strong>.  A tree will be planted on Tar Beach in their name.\n\n<strong>Thanks most of all to our wonderful teachers, administrators, custodial and cafeteria staff who are the core of our “family under one sky!”</strong>\n\n<strong>Congrats to our fifth graders on their Moving Up from CWS and acceptance into middle school:  among them are ICE, Tompkins Square, Salk, TASS, Quest, PS318, and East Side Community High School.</strong>\n\n<strong>Where do CWS alumni go to college? </strong>In no particular order, Children’s Workshop School alumni are attending or have graduated from:   <strong>Bard, Hunter, Baruch, Hampshire, Carnegie Mellon, Ohio State, SUNY-Binghampton, Cornell, Oberlin, University of Montana, University of Toronto, SUNY-New Paltz, West Point, Bennington, SUNY-Fredonia, New England Conservatory of Music,  SUNY-Purchase,  University of Pittsburgh!</strong>\n\n<strong><em>Week of 3 June:</em></strong>\n\n1-8 June—Barnes and Noble Book Fair benefitting the CWS library! 20% of sales will be used to buy new books!! Use code #11114907\n\nWeds 5 June-PTA Executive Board meeting in Library Conference Room after drop-off\n\nThursday 6 June—no school citywide—Chancellor’s Day\n\n<strong><em>Week of 10 June:</em></strong>\n\nMonday 10 June—1/2 day-11:30 dismissal\n\nWeds 12 June-in lobby at 8:40am—last PTA meeting of the year\n\nWeds 12 June in lobby at 4:30pm—Change the Stakes.org Discussion—childcare provided\n\nThurs 13 June—3/4/5 Grade Talent Show –be on the lookout for details in backpacks\n\nFri 14 June—last School Leadership Team meeting of the year—7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\nFri 14 June:  Crayola Storm Day!!  Also:   Hip Hop Club and The Experimental Dance Group will perform at Community Meeting.  Congrats to Rew and her Guitar Club for a rockin’ performance at Community Meeting on 8 June!\n\n<strong><em>Week of 17 June—LAST WEEK OF AFTER-SCHOOL CLUBS</em></strong>\n\nWeds 19 June—5<sup>th</sup> Graders Moving Up Ceremony\n\nThurs 20 June—Party at Gnocco for Maria, celebrating her 20<sup>th</sup> anniversary as co-founder and principal of CWS!  4:30-6:30 $25 per person for food/$5 drinks. Kids are free!\n\nFri 21 June—all school picnic in East River Park and last day of clubs\n\n<strong><em>Week of 24 June:</em></strong>\n\nWeds 26 June-last day of school! ½ day—HAPPY AND SAFE SUMMER TO ALL!\n\n<strong>The first day of school is Weds 9 September.  Expect your child(ren) to receive a letter from their teacher at the end of August.  Any questions/concerns/ideas email </strong><a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\"><strong>ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</strong></a><strong>.  Check childrensworkshopschool.org from time to time during the summer for any updates!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Update for June 2013','','publish','open','open','','update-for-june-2013','','','2013-06-11 10:02:41','2013-06-11 14:02:41','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=874',0,'post','',0),(135,1,'2012-09-25 05:19:47','2012-09-25 05:19:47','','willow_tree_111110','','inherit','open','open','','willow_tree_111110','','','2012-09-25 05:19:47','2012-09-25 05:19:47','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/willow_tree_111110.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(834,1,'2013-04-29 15:02:49','2013-04-29 19:02:49','Thank you to all who helped out and attended Schoolapalooza--we had a wonderful, memorable evening celebrating 20 years of The Children\'s Workshop School and Maria as principal/founder!  Thanks especially to:  Kim, Ian, Rachel, Nancy, Cassy, Rina, Evan, Melissa,  Lori, Stephanie, Rodrigo, Frank, Dorothy, Judy, Roxanne, Williams, Sean, Nicole, Elizabeth, Beth, Scott, Chris, Keiko, Holly, Ken, Amy, Valerie, Tiffany, Eric, Paul, William, Michelle, Dan, Tomo, Sayoko, Heather, Oliver, Jed--thank you one and all!','Schoolapalooza Thank Yous','','publish','open','open','','schoolapalooza-thank-yous','','','2013-04-29 15:02:49','2013-04-29 19:02:49','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=834',0,'post','',0),(838,1,'2013-05-01 07:14:46','2013-05-01 11:14:46','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/the-childrens-workshop-schools-19th-annual-arts-and-science-fair-saturday-11-may-11-3-in-the-school-yard-see-you-there/artsandscienceposter2013a/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-839\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-839\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ARTSANDSCIENCEPOSTER2013A-550x710.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"710\" /></a>','The Children\'s Workshop School\'s 19th Annual Arts and Science Fair--Saturday 11 May 11-3 in the School Yard--See you there!!','','publish','open','open','','the-childrens-workshop-schools-19th-annual-arts-and-science-fair-saturday-11-may-11-3-in-the-school-yard-see-you-there','','','2013-05-01 07:14:46','2013-05-01 11:14:46','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=838',0,'post','',0),(843,1,'2013-05-01 12:57:52','2013-05-01 16:57:52','<strong>                                           The Children’s Workshop School Update\nFor the Month of May 2013\n</strong>                                           http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\nphone numbers:212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376\n”We’re all a family under one sky!”\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/cws-update-for-may-2013-arts-and-science-fair-saturday-11-may-11-330-in-the-school-yard/artsandscienceposter2013a1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-844\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-844\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ARTSANDSCIENCEPOSTER2013A1-550x710.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"710\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Schoolapalooza was amazing—thank you to all who volunteered and attended and partied.  We had a wonderful, memorable evening celebrating 20 years of The Children’s Workshop School and Maria as principal/founder!  Thanks especially to:  Kim, Ian, and Rachel for co-chairing;  Nancy and Cassy for coordinating the auction; and Rina, Evan, Melissa, Lori, Stephanie, Rodrigo, Frank, Dorothy, Judy, Roxanne, Williams, Sean, Nicole, Elizabeth, Beth, Scott, Chris, Keiko, Holly, Ken, Amy, Valerie, Tiffany, Eric, Paul, William, Michelle, Dan, Tomo, Sayoko, Heather, Oliver, Marty and Jed for their help before, during and after!  Thank you to Ciao for Now, Brooklyn Brewery, Matilda and Union Pool for their generous food and drink donations!  Thank you to Terry and her quintet, the Demolition String Band and Lisa Lisa for their performances!</strong>\n\n<strong>Now—get ready (quickly!) for the 19<sup>th</sup> Annual Arts and Science Fair at school on Saturday 11 May from 11-3:30pm, a great day for the whole family</strong>.  Great food, arts and crafts, face painting, science projects, painting and planting flower pots, tie dye, nutrition table, rummage sale (clothes only!).  <strong>Hugs to Judy for chairing the committee-her 14<sup>th</sup> Arts and Science Fair.  Thanks to Rosie for designing the poster! </strong>To help out, email Judy: <a href=\"mailto:garnar-wortzel@att.net\">garnar-wortzel@att.net</a>\n\n<strong>Thanks to Melissa for writing a winning Hurricane Sandy grant—we are awarded $3000 to help revive the hurricane-damaged Campos Community Garden,</strong> a wonderful springtime project for our students.\n\n<strong>What is your bright idea?—for our school, for our school building?</strong>  Add your idea to the wall-hanging over the entrance to our much-missed auditorium (renovations should be complete in time for school to start in September).  Look for stickies in one of the attached lunch bags and make your suggestion!  Thanks to Camille, EVCS PA president for making the wall hanging.\n\n<strong>The CD of Community Meeting songs will be finished soon, complete with a booklet of lyrics!  Thanks to our students, Gary, Elizabeth, Tiffany and Mario at Tu Casa Recording Studios.</strong>\n\n<strong>Club News from Darryl:</strong>  The Mural Club has started painting our mural in the Campos Garden just on the other side of the school yard! It is so exciting and is going to be beautiful, meaningful, and an uplifting presence for the whole neighborhood! The theme this year is \"Love the Earth, Love our City-Stop Pollution!\" Painting Projects continues to go outside and paint beautiful cityscapes. Choice Time Club is enjoying going outside as the weather gets warm and have been making collages, bookmarks, and colorful masks.\n\n<strong>More Club News:</strong>  The Creative Movement/Improvisational Dance Club, led by Patrizia, performed three beautiful and moving pieces at Community Meeting.  The Hip Hop Club will soon share a “Thriller” of a performance at an upcoming Community Meeting.\n\n<strong>Congrats to Mr. Scott’s Experimental Dance Group on being featured in an article in <em>The Wall Street Journal</em>.</strong>  The group will perform two shows in May, one at the Theatre for the New City as part of the Lower East Side Dance Festival—be on the lookout for more dates/times!\n\n<strong>The Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our beautiful library will be 3, 4, 5 June!</strong>\n\n<strong>The fifth graders will soon be off on their Washington, DC trip!</strong>\n\n<strong>Reminder for parents who drive their kids to school:  Please be mindful of the buses—do not park in front of the school.  It is best to park on a side street and walk over to school.</strong>\n\n<strong>A word about late passes</strong>: parent volunteers write late passes in the lobby after the last class has gone upstairs to their classroom.  If your child arrives to school late, s/he must get a late pass or else runs the risk of being marked absent for the day.  It is better to be marked late than absent (especially when s/he is in school!).\n\n<strong><em>Week of 6 May:</em></strong>\n\nWeds 8 May-PTA Executive Board meeting in the Library Conference Room after drop-off\n\nSat 11 May:  The Arts and Science Fair in the lobby, cafeteria and school yard—see you there!—a fun day for the whole family\n\n<strong><em>Week of 13 May:</em></strong>\n\nWeds 15 May:  PTA General Meeting at 6pm in the lobby\n\nFri 17 May—SLT meeting at 7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\n<strong><em>Week of 20 May:</em></strong>\n\nA quiet week at CWS!\n\n<strong><em>Week of 27 May:</em></strong>\n\nMon 27 May:  Memorial Day—no school!  Welcome summer!\n\nWeds 29 May:  all-school lice check\n\nFriday 31 May: Dress Up Day:  Sports Day\n\n<strong><em>Looking Forward!!!</em></strong>\n\nThurs 6 June—no school\n\nMon 10 June—1/2 day\n\nWeds 12 June:  PTA General meeting after drop-off in the lobby\n\nThurs 13 June—3/4/5 grade Talent Show\n\nFri 14 June—Crayola Storm Day\n\nFri 21 June-last day of after school clubs\n\nWeds 26 June—last day of school –1/2 day\n\nMonday 9 September—first day of school','CWS Update for May 2013--Arts and Science Fair, Saturday 11 May 11-3:30 in the school yard!','','publish','open','open','','cws-update-for-may-2013-arts-and-science-fair-saturday-11-may-11-330-in-the-school-yard','','','2013-05-01 12:57:52','2013-05-01 16:57:52','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=843',0,'post','',0),(132,1,'2011-10-01 09:00:04','2011-10-01 09:00:04','On Saturday, Oct 1st, 2011, Chico, the community\'s legendary graffiti artist adorned the walls of CWS. He turned the whole third floor into an underwater fantasy. The next Saturday, parents and teachers, staff, volunteers from Now It\'s Your Turn, and Check Point Software Technologies Ltd., volunteered to varnish over the paintings and to paint another floor\'s walls. Thank you to Chico and to our wonderful volunteers for making our school so beautiful.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_chico2.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"CWS_chico2\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWS_chico2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"299\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://manhattan.ny1.com/content/top_stories/148173/chico-paints-final-mural-in-east-village-school\" target=\"_blank\">CWS and Chico were featured in a NY1 interview. To view the interview, click here&gt;&gt;</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://manhattan.ny1.com/content/top_stories/148173/chico-paints-final-mural-in-east-village-school\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-89\" title=\"CWSonNY1\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWSonNY1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"873\" /></a>\n<div></div>','10/1/2011 Chico paints a mural in CWS','','publish','open',