',0,'post','',0),(967,1,'2013-09-26 16:13:36','2013-09-26 20:13:36','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/the-childrens-workshop-school-second-re-annual-harvest-festival-saturday-19-october/cwsharvestfestival2013-1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-968\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-968\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-229x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nHarvest Festival pricing:  Food will vary in price.  POP (pay-one-price)  for activities:  $15 for 1 child/$20 for 2 children/$25 for 3+ children (must be from same family; cousins not included!  spit sisters/blood brothers not included!)  OR pay per activity, $1 per ticket (# of tix per activity will vary)\n\nTo volunteer to help out at the Harvest Festival, please email Rina rinaortega4@gmail.com or Elizabeth edowner@earthlink.net.\n\n&nbsp;','The Children\'s Workshop School Second Re-Annual Harvest Festival!  Saturday 19 October','','publish','open','open','','the-childrens-workshop-school-second-re-annual-harvest-festival-saturday-19-october','','','2013-09-26 16:13:36','2013-09-26 20:13:36','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=967',0,'post','',0),(986,1,'2013-10-04 16:32:35','2013-10-04 20:32:35','Please note the Tech Team met and reconsidered the date of the Mixer/PTA Meeting, changing it from Fri 11 Oct to Mon 28 October from  6-8pm--no childcare provided (the other evening PTA meetings will have childcare).','Change of date for Tech Team-sponsored Mixer/PTA Meeting:  now Monday 28 October 6-8pm','','publish','open','open','','change-of-date-for-tech-team-sponsored-mixerpta-meeting-now-monday-28-october-6-8pm','','','2013-10-04 16:32:35','2013-10-04 20:32:35','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=986',0,'post','',0),(988,1,'2013-10-08 12:25:20','2013-10-08 16:25:20','<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/october-update/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-989\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-989\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/cwsharvestfestival2013-1-229x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For October 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">212-614-9531 or <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<strong>October will be a wonderful month for CWS!</strong>  Now that our children are settled into their classroom routines, having formed the all-important bond with their teachers and classmates, we can come together as a community to square dance, make crafts and eat great food at <strong>our Second Re-Annual Harvest Festival on Saturday 19 October from 11-3.  Bring friends and family—all are welcome!  </strong>Later in the month will be the <strong>Technology Team-sponsored Mixer/PTA Meeting starting at 6:00pm on Monday 28 October—adults only!</strong>\n\nThank you to Joyce, Sonia, Jed and Christopher for providing childcare on <strong>Curriculum Night</strong> and to Judy and Ian for making the snack run.  Thank you to Hope for writing the CWS Safety Brochure.\n\nDorothy has the <strong>library </strong>up and running-thank you to those parents who have volunteered to shelve books and help maintain the library’s collection.  Please be sure your child(ren) return their library contracts.\n\nPlease <strong>return lunch forms to the office</strong>, if you have not already.  If you need another copy, please see Dorothy in the library.  Also, fifth grade parents, if you have not already spoken with Dorothy about the middle school application process, please visit her in the library or email her: dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov.\n\nCongrats to Angie and Kaylee, both in Molly’s class—they each won a Rainbow Loom!  Be on the lookout for <strong>more PTA raffles—Minecraft Legos!</strong>—every single penny goes right back to our children.  Coming up in a month or so: <strong>we will raffle off  2 tickets to see the Little Orchestra Society’s production of <em>Firebird</em>  at Lincoln Center (Sun 24 Nov at noon—1 hour long--perfect for ages 4+--excellent seats---$50 value).</strong>\n\n<strong>Coffee And…the Book Sale</strong> is (almost) every Friday before Community Meeting, thanks to Melissa, Natalie, Roxanne, Sayoko and the many parents who donate.\n\n<strong><em>Great news!:  we will have air conditioners by May/June in every classroom—in the library—in the office!—all thanks to our After-School Clubs budget surplus.</em></strong>\n\nThank you to the Manhattan Borough President’s office, which has supplied our teachers with <strong>Youth Bucks coupons redeemable for $2 worth of Union Square Greenmarket produce</strong>. Classes will be taking walks to the Greenmarket to spend their bucks.\n\nOur first school-wide lice check of the year will be on 8 Oct.  Thank you to Nancy for coordinating and Judy, Rachel and Lori for helping out.  Remember, there is no shame or blame when it comes to lice and the sooner we get rid of them, the less likely they will spread.\n\nPlease tell your <strong>3/4/5<sup>th</sup> graders to be on the lookout for classroom visits from Ed, our CWS Band Director (18 years and counting!) and Terry, our Turtle Bay Music School teacher</strong>, as they will invite the children to join the <strong>Band and Chorus</strong>, both of which meet during school hours<strong>.  No experience necessary</strong>—all 3/4/5<sup>th</sup> grade students are eligible to join Chorus or Band <strong>(instruments supplied by our school</strong>, thanks in part to a VH-1 grant).  Those who join must commit to <strong>regular and dedicated practice</strong>! Once the Band is organized, we would like a parent to serve as Band Parent and help coordinate communication between Ed and band members.\n\n<strong>Thank you to Bent on Learning, </strong>our yoga program:  <strong>Bent on Learning  is hosting a fundraiser for CWS--Friday 18 October from 6:30-9pm at The Shala Union Square, 815 Broadway, second floor; $50 suggested donation.  </strong>6:30-7:30 participate in a vinyasa/restorative class then at 7:45 enjoy music by Charlie Burnham, a singer and violinist.\n\n<strong>Swim classes will start 15 October for the 2<sup>nd</sup> graders</strong> at the Asser Levy pool on 23<sup>rd</sup> Street, thanks to the NYC Department of Parks and Recreation Swim for Life program.  <strong>The third graders have started doing Reading Buddies with the pre-k children</strong>—Molly’s students are matched with Suma’s students and Miriam’s students are matched with Helen’s.\n\nCheck out the <strong>New York Public Library’s list of 100 Great Children’s Books (in abc order)</strong>:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.nypl.org/childrens100\">http://www.nypl.org/childrens100</a>\n\n<strong>Turtle Bay Music School is having its annual Halloween Open House on Sat 26 Oct from 12-3</strong> at 244 East 52 Street between 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> Avenues—take 6 or M trains or M15 bus.  To RSVP(and you must rsvp), fill out form in link:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.tbms.org/event/halloween-open-house/\">http://www.tbms.org/event/halloween-open-house/</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><em>WEEK of 5 October:</em></strong>\n\nAll week long is <strong>Parents as Partners Week</strong>, sponsored by the NYC Department of Education—Chancellor Walcott scheduled to speak on 10 Oct--see all activities/meetings here.\n\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/ParentsFamilies/ParentsasPartnersOctober2013\">http://schools.nyc.gov/ParentsFamilies/ParentsasPartnersOctober2013</a>\n\nTues 8 October:  All-school lice check\n\n<strong><em>Week of 14 October:</em></strong>\n\nMon 14 October—no school-Columbus Day\n\nFriday 18 October—School Leadership Team meeting 7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\n<strong><em>Saturday 19 October—Harvest Festival!  11-3 in the school yard, cafeteria and lobby—rain or shine! Harvest Festival pricing: entry is free; entertainment is free. Food will vary in price. POP (pay-one-price) for activities: $15 for 1 child/$20 for 2 children/$25 for 3+ children (must be from same family; cousins not included! spit sisters/blood brothers not included!) OR pay per activity, $1 per ticket (# of tix per activity will vary)</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Week of 21 October:</strong>\n\nWeds 23 October:  picture day!  Do not wear green! (Please note that Miriam’s and Chrystal’s classes will take their all-class photos on 15 October)\n\nThursday 24 October:  no school for pre-k\n\n<strong>Week of 28 October:</strong>\n\n<strong><em>Monday 28 October Tech Team-sponsored PTA Mixer/Meeting 6-8pm in lobby.  This is a child-free event; our only one of the school year.</em></strong>\n\nPlease note that<strong> at The Children’s Workshop School, we do not honor any holidays other than birthdays and Martin Luther King Day (with our All-School Living the Dream Celebration). Please do not send your child(ren) to school in costume on Halloween</strong>—have a great time celebrating Halloween after school.\n\n<strong><em>Looking Forward…the November update will go out in mailchimp, thanks to the efforts of Veronica and Keiko:</em></strong>\n\n5 Nov-Election Day, no school\n\n6 Nov-PTA Exec Board Meeting in Library Conference Room after drop-off\n\n11 Nov-Veteran’s Day-no school\n\n13 Nov-PTA General Meeting after drop-off in lobby (note change of date from 20 Nov)\n\n22 Nov-half day for Staff Weekend Retreat-pickup time TBA\n\n28 and 29 Nov-no school—Happy Thanksgiving!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','October Update','','publish','open','open','','october-update','','','2013-10-08 12:25:20','2013-10-08 16:25:20','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=988',0,'post','',0),(924,1,'2013-08-26 10:01:31','2013-08-26 14:01:31','<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/latest-photo-of-the-auditorium-wow/photo-5/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-925\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-925\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-5-224x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\nThanks to Joyce for documenting the progress and to the team of renovators!','Latest Photo of the Auditorium:  Wow!','','publish','open','open','','latest-photo-of-the-auditorium-wow','','','2013-08-26 10:01:31','2013-08-26 14:01:31','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=924',0,'post','',0),(952,1,'2013-09-11 16:29:06','2013-09-11 20:29:06','Please join us for the Welcome Breakfast and first PTA meeting of the school year on Friday 13 September after drop-off!  Enjoy coffee, thanks to the generosity of Porto Rico, and treats, thanks to the generosity of our longtime families.  Meet the PTA executive board,  committee chairs and our teachers and staff.  Find out the many ways your family can contribute to CWS!','PTA Welcome Breakfast/First PTA Meeting on Friday 13 September after drop-off','','publish','open','open','','pta-welcome-breakfastfirst-pta-meeting-on-friday-13-september-after-drop-off','','','2013-09-11 16:29:06','2013-09-11 20:29:06','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=952',0,'post','',0),(959,1,'2013-09-24 07:26:59','2013-09-24 11:26:59','Wednesday, 2 October is Curriculum Night--childcare provided\n\nFriday, 11 October from 6-8 in the lobby  is the Technology Team-sponsored PTA Mixer/Meeting--adults only\n\nSaturday 19 October is the Second Re-Annual Children\'s Workshop School Harvest Festival!  Make a scarecrow-- paint a pumpkin---squaredance--eat great food!  To volunteer to help out, email Rina rinaortega4@gmail.com or Elizabeth edowner@earthlink.net\n\n&nbsp;','SAVE THE DATES!!','','publish','open','open','','save-the-date-saturday-19-october-is-the-harvest-festival'