d Noble Union Square.  bottom photo:  Patrizia\'s Improvisational Dance Club performs at Community Meeting)\n\n<strong>Thank you to Nicole for organizing a fantastic Barnes and Noble Book Fair</strong>--and to the Michael Mutt Gallery Love Yourself origami heart project--and to the many authors who read and to the families and friends of The Children\'s Workshop School who attended!\n\nThank you to our teachers for giving a <strong>test prep information session</strong> to parents yesterday morning, 10 Feb--and to the members of the Advocacy Committee who led a discussion afterwards about the many issues surrounding high-stakes testing.  More Advocacy Committee meetings will be scheduled in the coming weeks.\n\n<strong>PTA Meeting Weds 12 Feb at 6pm in the Library:</strong>  childcare and pizza (for kids only) provided.  Dorothy will lead a mini-workshop for parents, using our new laptops, about how to search the library\'s online catalogue, then we will follow our regular agenda.\n\n<strong>Community Meeting on Friday 14 Feb:  The Guitar Club, led by Rew, will perform!</strong>\n\nENJOY YOUR WINTER BREAK! NO SCHOOL MON 17 FEB TIL FRI 21 FEB. SEE YOU MON 24 FEB!\n\n<strong>Friday 28 February:  half -day--12:10 dismissal.  Third graders perform at Community Meeting and it\'s also Crayola Storm Day!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','PTA Meeting 12 Feb at 6:00pm in the Library and Half-Day on Fri 28 Feb','','publish','open','open','','pta-meeting-12-feb-at-600pm-in-the-library-and-half-day-on-fri-28-feb','','','2014-02-11 07:22:49','2014-02-11 12:22:49','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1152',0,'post','',0),(502,1,'2012-09-29 07:28:42','2012-09-29 07:28:42','','winterCraftFair4','','inherit','open','open','','wintercraftfair4','','','2012-09-29 07:28:42','2012-09-29 07:28:42','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/winterCraftFair4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(503,1,'2012-09-29 07:28:43','2012-09-29 07:28:43','','winterCraftFair3','','inherit','open','open','','wintercraftfair3','','','2012-09-29 07:28:43','2012-09-29 07:28:43','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/winterCraftFair3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(504,1,'2012-09-29 07:28:45','2012-09-29 07:28:45','','winterCraftFair2','','inherit','open','open','','wintercraftfair2','','','2012-09-29 07:28:45','2012-09-29 07:28:45','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/winterCraftFair2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(505,1,'2012-09-29 07:28:46','2012-09-29 07:28:46','','winterCraftFair1','','inherit','open','open','','wintercraftfair1','','','2012-09-29 07:28:46','2012-09-29 07:28:46','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/winterCraftFair1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(514,1,'2012-09-29 07:42:43','2012-09-29 07:42:43','','German_orchestra_flyer','','inherit','open','open','','german_orchestra_flyer','','','2012-09-29 07:42:43','2012-09-29 07:42:43','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/German_orchestra_flyer.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(515,1,'2012-09-29 07:42:44','2012-09-29 07:42:44','','german_orchestra','','inherit','open','open','','german_orchestra-2','','','2012-09-29 07:42:44','2012-09-29 07:42:44','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/german_orchestra1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(525,1,'2012-10-10 02:54:30','2012-10-10 02:54:30','','Harvest Festival 2012','','inherit','open','open','','print-5','','','2012-10-10 02:54:30','2012-10-10 02:54:30','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/cwsharvestfestival2012.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1235,1,'2014-05-14 21:29:43','2014-05-15 01:29:43','<!--[if gte vml 1]&gt;-->\n\n<!--[if !vml]-->\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1245\" alt=\"Schoola poster event J rgb S\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Schoola-poster-event-J-rgb-S-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></p>\nThe Children\'s Workshop School (CWS) announces its 21st annual charity event, <strong><i>SCHOOLAPALOOZA!</i>, being held on Friday, May 30<sup>th</sup> at the Paul Taylor Dance Company Studios, 551 Grand Street</strong> on the Lower East Side. This not-to-be-missed event includes live music featuring headliner LES legend <strong>Lisa Lisa of Lisa Lisa and the Cult Jam,</strong> a silent auction and excellent cuisine, all to benefit a wonderful and dynamic East Village public grammar school with a mission of diversity and social justice.\n\nThe CWS parents and community redefine the school fundraiser by reaching out to a broad network of talented friends and family to host one of the spring’s best parties. <strong>Enjoy dinner prepared by award-winning chef Stephanie Sugawara while being entertained by musical guests The Lonesome Cupcakes and The Brown Rice Family, 2013 winner of WNYC\'S Battle of the Bands.</strong>\n\nThe silent auction list includes <strong>artworks by Jason Rohlf, Oliver Michaels, STASH, Grotesk, and Darryl LaVare; vacation homes in Costa Rica, the Bahamas and Tuscany; fashion by CWS mother and Pipsqueak Chapeau proprietor Sveta Drescher</strong> as well as handbags and sunglasses by Chanel and Kate Spade, private dinner parties, sailing trips, sewing lessons, and more. Each purchase supports a great educational institution.\n\nThe event starts at 6 pm Friday, May 30th --Lisa Lisa usually performs around 9:00.  Tickets sold at the door!  $25 --buy 2 get one free<a title=\"CWS Schoolapalooza Website\" href=\"http://www.schoola.org\">\n</a>\n\n<b>This year Schoolapalooza enters the 21st Century! The auction will be fully digital, making bidding and checkout stress free. </b>\n\n<b>-Register ahead of time online! </b>\n\n<b> </b><b>-Check out auction items on our</b>\n\n<b>website:  </b><a href=\"http://www.24fundraiser.com/schoolapalooza\">www.24fundraiser.com/schoolapalooza</a><b></b>\n\n<b> </b><b>-Friends and family can bid from afar!</b>\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>Thank you to Judy and Elizabeth for co-chairing a wonderful Arts and Science Fair</strong>--the school\'s 20th and Judy\'s 15th!--a great time was had by all.  Thanks to our teachers and administrators: Joyce, Maria, Dorothy, Jen, Molly and Miriam; Officer Baptiste; Chris and his custodial staff; parents Peter, Lori, Holly, Mike, Paul, Jill, Rina, Jill, Sayoko, Tomo, Roka, Shahad and family, Tiffany, Steve, Hope, Beth, Sean, Melissa, Tom, Margot, Gabby and her mom, Risa, Jen, Mo, Nancy, Rosie, Theresa, Rick, Ann, Sabine, Satya, Mike, Chris and Andrew.</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\"><strong>Friday 16 May: half-day 11:30 dismissal.</strong></span>  If you need childcare, talk to Joyce: Esther is running her Half Day Camp today, as well as 3 June and 9 June half days.  The fifth graders will do a Westward Expansion presentation at Community Meeting and we will also honor Bent on Learning yoga and The Shala yoga studio for their wonderful yoga program, enjoyed by all CWS students.\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600\"><strong>Thank you to Rosella, Pierluigi, Ciara and Ilaria for donating a delicious catered lunch from Cafe Pick Me Up for our teachers to enjoy on 16 May!</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #008000\"><strong>Friday 16 May at 6pm:  The Children\'s Workshop School Chorus, led by Terry,  will perform at The Tutle Bay Music School</strong></span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Tues 20 May:  Valerie, our pre-k social worker, will lead a workshop after drop-off about Making Tranisitions--open to parents and family members of children in every grade</span>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080\">Weds 21 May:  PTA MEETING--6PM IN THE LOBBY--childcare provided and pizza for kids too</span></strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #000080\">Saturday 24 May: Mr. Scott\'s Experimental Dance Group (EDG) performs at The Theater for the New City at 2pm</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #008000\">Monday 26 May--Memorial Day-No School--Welcome Summer!</span>\n\nFriday 30 May at Community Meeting--Molly\'s class performs\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;text-decoration: underline\">FRIDAY 30 MAY-SCHOOLAPALOOZA AT PAUL TAYLOR DANCE COMPANY --551 Grand Street--6-10pm</span></span></strong>\n\n<strong><em> Looking forward to June:</em></strong>\n\nTues 3 June--half day--11:30 dismissal.  Esther\'s Half Day Club pick up at 5.\n\nWeds 4 June--PTA executive board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\nWeds 4 June--District 1 Diversity Meeting--after drop-off at PS 15 at 333 East 4th Street (between Aves C and D)\n\nWeds 4 June--CWS 3/4/5 Grade Talent Show Auditions after school\n\nThurs 5 June-Chancellor\'s Day-no school\n\nFriday 6 June at Community Meeting--Rew\'s Guitar Club performs\n\nMon 9 June-half day--11:30 dismissal.  Esther\'s Half Day Club pick up at 5.\n\nFriday 13 June at Community Meeting--Mr. Scott\'s Experimental Dance Group (EDG) and Tiana\'s Hip Hop Club perform\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">16-20 June--LAST WEEK OF CLUBS!</span> </strong> Thank you to Joyce, Rachel and Darryl for directing the clubs and to all our club leaders for giving CWS kids such wonderful experiences\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Weds 18 June--PTA meeting after drop off in the lobby --elections for 14/15 school  year PTA executive board</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #000080\">Thurs 19 June--All-School Picnic and Field Day at the giant playground in East River Park--all members of the CWS community encouraged to attend!</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Fri 20 June--Moving Up Ceremony</span></strong>--Congrats to our fifth graders who will move up to middle schools, among them:   Tompkins Square Middle School, I.C.E., TASS, East Side Community High School (grades 6-12), School of the Future, Lab and Salk.\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Weds 25 June--3/4/5 Grade Talent Show at 5:30pm--The CWS Band will also perform!</span></strong>\n\n<em><strong><span style=\"color: #008080\">Thursday 26 June -last day of school!</span> </strong></em>Happy summer!  Public pools open 27 June--free lunch available to kids all summer long at the pools--Tompkin Square; Dry Dock; Hamilton Fish; among others--also free swimming classes for kids at the public pools!\n\n<strong><em>Looking forward to next school year 14/15:</em></strong>\n\n4 September is the first day of school\n\nSaturday 20 September 11-3:  Centennial Celebration of the Anna Howard Shaw School Building--all 3 schools in the building collaborating on a family fun day!\n\nThanksgiving Recess--27 Nov\n\nWinter Holiday Recess--24 Dec-2 Jan\n\nWinter Break--16 Feb-20 Feb\n\nSpring Break--3 April-10 April\n\nLast day of school--26 June 2015\n\n<!--[endif]--><!--[if gte vml 1]&gt;-->\n\n<!--[if !vml]--><!--[endif]-->','Schoolapalooza--30 May at the Paul Taylor Dance Company Studios!','','publish','open','open','','schoolapalooza-30-may-at-the-paul-taylor-dance-company-studios','','','2014-05-14 21:29:43','2014-05-15 01:29:43','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1235',0,'post','',0),(546,3,'2012-10-10 00:38:23','2012-10-10 04:38:23','','constructionSept2012-1','September 2012: First steps of the demolition in the auditorium.','inherit','open','open','','constructionsept2012-1','','','2012-10-10 00:38:23','2012-10-10 04:38:23','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-1.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(547,3,'2012-10-10 00:38:26','2012-10-10 04:38:26','','constructionSept2012-2','','inherit','open','open','','constructionsept2012-2','','','2012-10-10 00:38:26','2012-10-10 04:38:26','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-2.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(548,3,'2012-10-10 00:38:29','2012-10-10 