4:26','2014-06-04 11:54:26','<strong>Thank you to Cassy, Rachel, Tiffany, Rina, Evan, Stephanie, and everyone who volunteered and attended Schoolapalooza!   It was a great success and a fantastic party--thank you to Paul Taylor Dance Company Studios for hosting us in such a beautiful space and The Lonely Cupcakes, The Brown Rice Family and Lisa Lisa for performing!  It was great to see the many alumni parents who attended, as well as Maria\'s co-founder, Jean and our partners from PS94-The Spectrum School.</strong>\n\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>All are welcome at the 3/4/5 Grade Talent Show on Weds 25 June --refreshments for sale in the lobby at 5:30; free show starts at 6pm in the auditorium (donations always welcome). The CWS Band, directed by Ed, in his 18th year!, The CWS Chorus, led by Terry, and Patrizia\'s Improvisational Dance Club will perform.  Also 10 more acts:  singing, dancing, gymnastics, violin, cello and piano playing, and  Rubik\'s Cube speed-unscrambling!  Thanks to Jen, Beth, Elizabeth , Scott and Robert for organizing.</strong></span>\n\n<strong><em><span style=\"color: #000000\">Important Dates in June:</span></em></strong>\n\nWeds 4 June–PTA executive board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Weds 4 June–District 1 Diversity Meeting–after drop-off at PS 15 at 333 East 4th Street (between Aves C and D)</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008080\">Weds 4 June–CWS 3/4/5 Grade Talent Show Auditions after school</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff00ff\">Thurs 5 June-Chancellor’s Day-no school</span></strong>\n\nFriday 6 June at Community Meeting–Rew’s Guitar Club performs\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080\">Mon 9 June-half day–11:30 dismissal.</span> </strong> Esther’s Half Day Club pick up at 5.\n\nFriday 13 June at Community Meeting–Mr. Scott’s Experimental Dance Group (EDG) and Tiana’s Hip Hop Club perform-plus slide show of the 5th graders\' trip to Washington, DC\n\n<strong>16-20 June–LAST WEEK OF CLUBS! </strong> <strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Thank you to Joyce, Rachel and Darryl for directing the clubs and to all our club leaders for giving CWS kids such wonderful experiences.</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff00ff\">Mon 16 June at 2pm--Centennial Celebration Committee meeting</span></strong>--get involved in planning a family-fun day, Sat 20 Sept, together with EVCS and PS94-The Spectrum School--to celebrate the 100th birthday of our school building.\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff6600\">Tues 17 June:  Arts Connection puppetry performance in the morning. 3/4/5 graders perform.  </span></strong>District 1 Diversity meeting at PS 20 on Houston and Essex Streets at 8:30am.  Step aside, Maria:  third grader Atticus will be Principal for the Day!\n\n<strong>Weds 18 June–PTA meeting after drop off in the lobby –elections for 14/15 school  year PTA executive board--breakfast served to thank the many 5th grade parents whose children are moving up to middle school who have done so much for all of our CWS children!</strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080\">Thurs 19 June–All-School Picnic and Field Day at the giant playground in East River Park–all members of the CWS community encouraged to attend!</span></strong>\n\n<strong>Fri 20 June–Moving Up Ceremony in the auditorium 9-11:30</strong>–Congrats to our fifth graders who will move up to middle schools, among them:   Tompkins Square Middle School, I.C.E (grades 6-12)., TASS, East Side Community High School (grades 6-12), School of the Future, Lab, Baruch and Salk.  After the Moving Up Ceremony, as is CWS tradition,  the fourth graders and their families will serve lunch to the fifth graders and their families.\n\nTues 24 June-pre-k and k orientation for new families\n\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Weds 25 June–3/4/5 Grade Talent Show at 5:30pm</span></strong>\n\n<em><strong>Thursday 26 June -last day of school, 11:30 dismissal! Thank you to Maria, Dorothy, Joyce, Sonia and all of our teachers and staff, our school safety officers, kitchen staff, and custodial staff for a wonderful year!  </strong></em>\n\nHappy summer!  Public pools open 27 June–free lunch available to kids all summer long at the pools–Tompkins Square; Dry Dock; Hamilton Fish; among others–also free swimming classes for kids at the public pools!\n\n<strong><em>Looking forward to next school year 14/15--teacher letters will be mailed out in late August:</em></strong>\n\n4 September is the first day of school\n\n4 and 5 September--join Dorothy and the PTA executive board for Coffee and Conversation on Tar Beach after drop off\n\n9 Sept (tentative)-CWS Tech Team Mixer--6-8pm--all parents invited --SmartBoard demonstration and refreshments on Tar Beach\n\n12 Sept (tentative)-first PTA meeting --after drop-off in lobby--meet our PTA committee chairs, School Leardership Team (SLT) members; teachers and staff\n\nSaturday 20 September 11-3:  Centennial Celebration of the Anna Howard Shaw School Building–all 3 schools in the building collaborating on a family fun day!\n\n25 and 26 Sept-no school -Rosh Hashanah\n\n13 Oct-no school-Columbus Day\n\n4 Nov-no school-Election Day\n\n11 Nov-no school-Veteran\'s Day\n\nThanksgiving Recess–27 and 28 Nov\n\nWinter Holiday Recess–24 Dec-2 Jan\n\n19 Jan-no school-Martin Luther King Day\n\nWinter Break–16 Feb-20 Feb\n\nSpring Break–3 April-10 April\n\n25 May-no school-Memorial Day\n\n4 June-no school-Chancellor\'s Day\n\nLast day of school–26 June 2015','3/4/5 Grade Talent Show-Weds 25 June at 5:30 --Last Week of Clubs: 16-20 June--All-School Picnic and Field Day 19 June','','publish','open','open','','345-grade-talent-show-weds-25-june-at-530-last-week-of-clubs-16-20-june','','','2014-06-04 07:54:26','2014-06-04 11:54:26','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1251',0,'post','',0),(1267,1,'2014-06-23 15:49:27','2014-06-23 19:49:27','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff\"><strong>The Children\'s Workshop School Congratulates and Celebrates Our Fifth Graders as They Move Up to Middle School</strong></span></p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1269\" alt=\"cwspuppets\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cwspuppets-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" />\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1268\" alt=\"ltdaward\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ltdaward-225x300.jpg\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" />Our fifth graders ended their memorable year with many wonderful events, including the amazing Arts Connection puppetry program Parade of Civil Rights Leaders,  the selection of the 21st annual Living the Dream Book Award, and their Moving Up Ceremony and luncheon made and served by the fourth graders and their families.\n\nIn collaboration with fifth graders from Manhattan Country School and Central Park East II, in a year-long process, CWS fifth graders chose a book, published in 2013, that embodies  Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr\'s vision of peace and social justice:  <em>Desmond and the Very Mean Word: A Story of Forgiveness</em>, written by Archbishop Desmond Tutu and Douglas Carlton Abrams and illustrated by A.G. Ford.   At the Living the Dream award celebration at the Schomburg Center for Research in Black Culture, Doug Abrams shared an email from <strong>Archbishop Tutu himself:</strong>\n\n<strong>“It is a great honor to receive your award celebrating the great American civil rights hero, Martin Luther King.  Each of you carry on his spirit and each of you will help make our world a place with more love and more forgiveness and where mean words are replaced with kind ones.  </strong>Doug accepts this award on both of our behalf, and we thank you from the bottom of our hearts.”\n\nCongrats again to our fifth graders who are moving up to middle schools, among them: Tompkins Square Middle School, I.C.E (grades 6-12)., TASS, East Side Community High School (grades 6-12), School of the Future, Lab, Baruch and Salk.\n\nCWS alumni graduating from high school or on summer break from college have been stopping by to say hi to their teachers and Maria, Dorothy and Joyce-- some of the high school they attend or have graduated from:  ICE, East Side Community High School, Beacon, Brooklyn Tech and NEST + M.  Some of the colleges they attend or will start at in the Fall:  SUNY-Potsdam, Cornell University, University of Pittsbugh, SUNY-Purchase, Hunter College, McGill University, Ithaca College, Borough of Manhattan Community College, and SUNY-Brockport.\n\nHere\'s photos of the recent Experimental Dance Group (directed by Mr. Scott)  and Hip Hop Club (led by Tiana)  performances at Community Meeting:\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1271\" alt=\"15 june 2014 036\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/15-june-2014-036-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1272\" alt=\"15 june 2014 030\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/15-june-2014-030-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />\n<div dir=\"ltr\">The PTA  Executive Board--Rina, Beth, Elizabeth, Heidi, Tiffany, Mo, Keiko and Shay--would like to thank the many parents, family, teachers and staff members who contribute their time and talents to our children and our school throughout the year!</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Office volunteers: Judy and Sayoko</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Late Pass Writers: Elizabeth, Nancy, Judy, Amy and Susan</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Library Volunteers: Nicole, Holly and Lamont</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Afterschool Clubs: Joyce, Rachel and Daryl</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">School Leadership Team (SLT): Judy (chair), Nicole, Satya, Ian, Ilan; teachers Molly, Suma, Susan, Crystal; Maria and Dorothy</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Technology Team: Keiko, Ian, teachers Susan, Jeff, Jessica, Scott and Crystal, and Dorothy</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Teacher Appreciation Luncheon Donation: Cafe Pick Me Up (Rossella and Pierluigi)</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Committee Chairs:</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Harvest Festival: Elizabeth and Rina</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">SCRIP Gift Cards: Tiffany and Marcia</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">KidsArt Notecards: Beverly and Joyce</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Holiday Craft Fair: Bari and Keiko</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Original Works: Jill and Nicole</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Barnes and Noble Book Fair: Nicole</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Fundraising and Grant Writing: Melissa</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Advocacy: Hope</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Lice Checks: Nancy</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Art and Science Fair: Judy and Elizabeth</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma;font-size: small\">Schoolapalooza: Cassy, Rachel, Tiffany, Rina, Evan, Stephanie</span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-fam