y and Daryl, co-secretaries; and Keiko and Natasha, co-treasurers.  Email us: ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1287\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"225\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1287 \" alt=\"Jason break-dancing!\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/26-june-2014-johns-camera-058-225x300.jpg\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /> Jason break-danci[/caption]\n\n<strong><em>Looking forward to next school year 14/15! Teacher letters will be mailed out in late August.  School hours will remain 8:40-3:00.  Please open the link in the right hand column for the Fall 2014 After School Clubs Brochure.</em></strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><em>  Important dates in September:</em></strong></p>\n4 September is the first day of school\n\n4 and 5 September–join Dorothy and the PTA executive board for Coffee and Conversation on Tar Beach after drop off\n\n9 Sept -CWS Tech Team Mixer–6-8pm–all parents invited –SmartBoard demonstration and refreshments on Tar Beach\n\n9 and 10 September–after school clubs registration in the morning before drop-off\n\n12 Sept - PTA and family orientation meeting –after drop-off in lobby–meet our PTA committee chairs, School Leardership Team (SLT) members; teachers and staff\n\n15 September–first day of after-school clubs.\n\n17 September–first District 1 Community Education Council meeting–Town Hall discussion of School Diversity\n\nSaturday 20 September 11-3:  Centennial Celebration of the Anna Howard Shaw School Building–all 3 schools in the building collaborating on a family fun day!\n\n25 and 26 Sept-no school -Rosh Hashanah\n\n&nbsp;\n<p align=\"center\"><b>Some Fun Stuff to Do This Summer</b></p>\nFREE (on weekends)—Governor’s Island—now open every day! $2 r/t ferry fare Mon-Fri.\n\nFREE-Brooklyn Bridge Park new public Pop-Up Pool and Pier 6 Playground\n\nNew York Historical Society—\"Madeline in New York: The Art of Ludwig Bemelmans\"\n\nMetropolitan Museum of Art—evening gown designer Charles James exhibit in The Costume Institute\n\nMuseum of the City of New York: “City as Canvas” and “Activist New York” exhibits\n\nAmerican Museum of Natural History: “The Power of Poison”; “Pterosaurus: Flight in the Age of Dinosaurs” and “Spiders Alive!”\n\nBrooklyn Children’s Museum: “Brooklyn Block Lab”\n\nFREE!-New York Public Library (42 and 5th): “The ABC of It: Why Children’s Books Matter”\n\nNew York Hall of Science: Science Playground, Rocket Park Mini Golf and Design Lab\n\nFREE- NYC Parks Summer Concerts\n\n<a href=\"http://www.nycgo.com/articles/free-summer-concerts-2014\">http://www.nycgo.com/articles/free-summer-concerts-2014</a>\n\nBrooklyn Cyclones or Staten Island Yankees game\n\nPublic pools (free lunch for kids at most locations) and the beach: Rockaway, Orchard Beach, Coney Island!','3/4/5 Grade Talent Show Photos--What CWS Families Need to Know for Back to School: Fall Clubs Brochure and September Dates--and Summer Fun Suggestions','','publish','open','open','','345-grade-talent-show-photos-what-cws-families-need-to-know-for-back-to-school-fall-clubs-brochure-and-september-dates-and-summer-fun-suggestions','','','2014-07-10 13:50:52','2014-07-10 17:50:52','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1282',0,'post','',0),(567,2,'2012-10-17 14:35:09','2012-10-17 18:35:09','','CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012','','inherit','open','open','','communitymeetinglobbyoct2012','','','2012-10-17 14:35:09','2012-10-17 18:35:09','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(574,2,'2012-10-18 12:43:35','2012-10-18 16:43:35','','OCT 2012 ALTERNATIVE Menu FINAL.xls','','inherit','open','open','','oct-2012-alternative-menu-final-xls','','','2012-10-18 12:43:35','2012-10-18 16:43:35','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/oct-2012-alternative-menu-final.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(575,2,'2012-10-18 12:44:10','2012-10-18 16:44:10','','OCT 2012 ALTERNATIVE Menu FINAL.xls','','inherit','open','open','','oct-2012-alternative-menu-final-xls-2','','','2012-10-18 12:44:10','2012-10-18 16:44:10','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/oct-2012-alternative-menu-final1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1404,1,'2014-10-01 11:44:31','2014-10-01 15:44:31','Families interested in The Children\'s Workshop School please sign up for a tour on the following dates by calling Joyce at 212-614-9531 x2091 or emailing her: jborden@schools.nyc.gov\n\nAll tours start at 8:15am and last til about 9:30.  You will meet the members of our school community:   teachers, parents, Maria, our principal, Joyce, our school secretary and Dorothy, our parent coordinator and observe classes.  We look forward to meeting you!\n\n21 October\n\n18 November\n\n2 December\n\n16 December\n\n6 January\n\n20 January\n\n3 February\n\n24 February','School Tour Dates','','publish','open','open','','school-tour-dates','','','2014-10-01 11:44:31','2014-10-01 15:44:31','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1404',0,'post','',0),(1416,1,'2014-10-08 15:59:47','2014-10-08 19:59:47','<strong><span style=\"color: #3366ff\">Thank you to alumni mom/artist Cathy and her crew of volunteer parents, especially Darryl, for their work restoring the artwork on Tar Beach (damaged from the scaffolding that encased our school building for 2 years)--the Bird of Imaging and the Labyrinth are nearly completely restored!</span></strong>\n<div><strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">Thank you to our volunteer late pass writers:  Judy, Elizabeth, Ian K. and Melissa--and to Judy and Sayoko for helping out in the office. Thank you to Tina for putting in a request to the city for new trees to be planted in front of the school building.</span></strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Our Grants Committee (Melissa, Tiffany, Lori, Rachel, Rina, Jessica, Tina) is hard at work applying for arts and movement grants--if you would like to get involved, please email Melissa: <a href=\"mailto:mvigilanteny@aol.com\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">mvigilanteny@aol.com</span></a>.  <em>Please attend the first Grants Committee meeting this Friday 10 October after Community Meeting if you can.</em></span></strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1422\" alt=\"harvestfestival2014 (1)\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/harvestfestival2014-1-230x300.jpg\" width=\"230\" height=\"300\" /></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong>Our first fundraiser of the year, the 3rd re-annual <span style=\"color: #ff0000\">CWS Harvest Festival is Sunday 26 October from 12-4</span>:  square dancing! bouncy castle! photo booth! face painting! decorate a fall leaf cookie! delicious food!  Volunteer your time and talents:  make cookies or mac and cheese or do facepainting or run an arts and crafts table or help set up and clean up---email Elizabeth <a href=\"mailto:edowner@earthlink.net\" target=\"_blank\">edowner@earthlink.net</a> or Rina <a href=\"mailto:rinaortega4@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">rinaortega4@gmail.com</a></strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">Be on the lookout for raffles--tickets on sale during Coffee And.. on Fridays in the lobby before Community Meeting!  Win 4 tickets to Sesame Place (plus free parking!)--win 2 tickets to see The Magic Flute at The New Victory Theater--win 3 tickets to see Jazz at Lincoln Center\'s Family Program: Who is Tito Puente?</span></strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>District One Middle School Fair tomorrow 9 Oct--School for Global Leaders 154 Stanton St --5:30-7:30pm</strong></span></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong> </strong></span></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>No school Monday 13 October-Happy Columbus Day</strong></span></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong> </strong></span></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>PTA Meeting--Tues 21 October after drop off in the lobby</strong></span></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><span style=\"color: #ff6600\"><strong>FREE FUN STUFF TO DO IN OCTOBER:</strong></span></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>New York Public Library for the Performing Arts at Lincoln Center new exhibit:  \"Somebody Come and Play:  45 Years of Sesame Street\"</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Saturday 18 October--Super Sabado!  Dia de los Muertos at El Museo del Barrio</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Sunday 19 October--Pickle Fest! on Orchard St and Delancey Street</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Saturday 25 October--Haunted High Line Halloween</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Saturday 25 October--Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div id=\":17u\"><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ssl.gstatic.com/ui/v1/icons/mail/images/cleardot.gif\" /></strong></span></div>\n</div>','Grants Committee meeting-Friday 10 Oct after Community Meeting.  Volunteer to help out at the Harvest Festival Sunday 26 October 12-4.  Also: fun FREE stuff to do in October','','publish','open','open','','grants-committee-meeting-friday-10-oct-after-community-meeting-volunteer-to-help-out-at-the-harvest-festival-sunday-26-october-12-4','','','2014-10-08 15:59:47','2014-10-08 19:59:47','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1416',0,'post','',0),(1429,1,'2014-10-20 14:32:08','2014-10-20 18:32:08','<strong><span style=\"color: #008000\">See you at the 3rd Re-Annual CWS Harvest Festival this Sunday 26 October:  bouncy castle, square dancing, photo booth, gardening at Campos Garden, games, crafts, great food!  Bring family and friends!  Thanks to Elizabeth and Rina for organizing the whole extravaganza and to Rosie for designing the poster:</span></strong>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1422\" alt=\"harvestfestival2014 (1)\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/harvestfestival2014-1-230x300.jpg\" width=\"230\" height=\"300\" />\n<p align=\"center\"><b>The Children’s Workshop School\n“Let’s Go See a Show!” Raffle</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>$2 per ticket/3 tickets for $5</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>WIN</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>2 tickets to see Mozart’s <i>The Magic Flute</i></b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b><i></i></b>performed by The Isango Ensemble from Cape Town, South Africa</p>\n<p align=\"center\">at The New Victory Theater on Sunday 9 November at Noon</p>\n<p align=\"center\">OR</p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>2 tickets to The Little Orchestra Society’s production of</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b> <i>The Four Seasons: A Spinning Planet</i> </b></p>\n<p align=\"center\">with Armitage Gone! Dance at</p>\n<p align=\"center\">New York City Center on Saturday 22 November at 11:00am</p>\n<p align=\"center\">OR</p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>3 tickets to the Jazz at Lincoln Center</b></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><b>Jazz for Young People Family Concert:  <i>Who is Tito Puente?</i></b></p>\n<p align=\"center\">featuring Wynton Marsalis</p>\n<p align=\"center\">at The Rose Theater on  Saturday 22 November at 3:00pm</p>\n<p align=\"center\"> Raffle tickets sold during Coffee And… 24, 31, Oct; 7 and 14 Nov with drawings at Community Meeting on 31 Oct (<i>The Magic Flute</i>) and 14 Nov (<i>The Four Seasons</i> and <i>Who is Tito Puente?</i>).  All proceeds benefit programs at CWS like Bent on Learning yoga,Turtle Bay Music School, The CWS Chorus, The CWS Band and more!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff\">SAVE THE DATE!!! SUNDAY 9 NOVEMBER AT 2PM AT BARNES AND NOBLE UNION SQUARE-</span></strong>-<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Kick off our Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our fantastic CWS library with Fred Schneider of The B-52s reading from <em>Sassafrass Jones and the Search for a Forever Home,</em> written by Cathleen Smith Bresciana,   Thanks to Nicole for organizing the book fair and thanks to Desiree from Barnes and Noble.</span></strong></p>','Harvest Festival-this Sunday 26 October!  November Raffles! Save the Date--Fred Schnieder of the B-52s doing a reading for the CWS Book Fair at Barnes and Noble Union Square-Sunday 9 November at 2pm','','publish','open','open','','harvest-festival-this-sunday-26-october-november-raffles-save-the-date-fred-schnieder-of-the-b-52s-doing-a-reading-for-the-cws-book-fair-at-barnes-and-noble-union-square-sunday-9-november-at-2pm','','','2014-10-20 14:32:08','2014-10-20 18:32:08','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1429',0,'post','',0),(1434,1,'2014-10-29 16:02:23','2014-10-29 20:02:23','<strong>Thank you to all who attended and helped out at The Harvest Festival this past Sunday--as always, we pulled together as a community and gave the children a wonderful fun day! </strong> Thanks especially to:\n<div>Elizabeth, Rina, Rina\'s mom, Beth, Daivd, Sayoko, Lori, Francisca, Veronica, Ms Capers, Cassy, Darryl and Scott, Kasumi, Eric, Marcel, Frank, Melissa, Rosie, Tiffany, Jay, Sabine, Daryl and Sean, Dorothy, Kathleen and Tom, Tomo, Tina, Mercedes, Nicole, Felix, Trina, Jen, Judy, Marcia, Maria, Monir\'s mom, Kerry-Ann, Cory, Johnny Pickles, Theresa, Luke, Tanthony, Paula, Hope, Lara and Sean, Mia, Maria, Mary, Jessica, Molly, Jeff, Seth, Julie, Loree, and Grandma Penny!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><strong><span style=\"color: #008080\">The Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our lovely CWS library is 5-12 November! Use code 11449717 at any Barnes and Noble store or online and Barnes and Noble will donate 20% of the sale to our school.  Come to the many readings--a highlight:  Fred Schnieder of The B-52s reading<em> Sassafrass Jones</em> at 2pm on 9 November at Barnes and Noble Union Square.  Thanks to Nicole for organizing with Desiree from Barnes and Noble and Jason for making the flyer:</span></strong></div>\n<div><img alt=\"cws fall book2014 (2)\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/cws-fall-book2014-2-550x711.jpg\" /></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<div id=\":18q\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ssl.gstatic.com/ui/v1/icons/mail/images/cleardot.gif\" /></div>\n<div>Melissa, Tina, Lori, Tiffany, Rachel and the Grants Committee have been hard at work--one initiative they have been working on is restoring the sidewalk space in front of the school building (damaged from the 2 years of scaffolding that enveloped the building)--a new tree will be planted, we will have garbage cans, tree guards and---more bike racks!\n<div></div>\n<div>Terry from Turtle Bay Music School has started music classes with all grades and The CWS Chorus with 3/4/5 graders.  The CWS Band has started up--Ed teaches 3/4/5 graders how to play flute, trumpet, trombone, etc during school time, so that every child who wants to  has the opportunity to learn an instrument.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Field trips!  Many classes have been taking trips to the Union Square Green Market.  The 1/2 classes also have visited Eldridge Street Synagogue, the 4th graders have gone on an immigration walk around Chinatown and soon will visit Inwood Hill Park.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Be on the lookout for a Hip Hop Club Holiday Performance--date TBA!\n<div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Check out the photo below from the Bent on Learning fundraiser at The Wild Horses of Sable Island Gallery on Grand Street--that\'s CWS student Yuri doing the frog pose on Alec Baldwin, with Franny and Chloe in the background.  The wonderful teachers from Bent on Learning bring yoga into our CWS  classrooms!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div><img alt=\"Yoga couple: Hilaria Baldwin perfermed a tripod headstand  while husband Alec stuck to a more basic  pose at the Bent On Learning Inspire gala at the Wild Horses Of Sable Island Gallery in New York on Thursday\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/10/24/1414130259042_wps_49_NEW_YORK_NY_OCTOBER_23_Hi.jpg\" /></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Sunday 9 November--Fred Schneider of The B-52s at Barnes and Noble Union Square reading from <em>Sassafrass Jones</em> at 2pm</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Tuesday 11 November--Veteran\'s Day--no school</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Weds 12 November--evening family conferences--no clubs</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Thurs 13 November--afternoon family conferences--NOON dismissal-no clubs.  Esther, our Karate Club leader, will hold a Half Day Club from 12-3.  Contact Joyce to sign up:  jborden@schools.nyc.gov</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Saturday 15 November-District One Diversity Workshop at PS 20 2:00-5:00--email Sally sallylee.abcd@gmail.com or Luke luke.henry@gmail.com to sign up to represent CWS at this important workshop</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Tuesday 18 November--school tour at 8:15am--PTA meeting after drop off in the lobby</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Friday 21 November--Schoolapalooza meeting after drop off in the lobby.  Look for Rachel or email her: rachel@dancewithrachel.com.  Schoolapalooza, our main fundraiser,  will be on Fri 24 April at the Murray Cantor Center on East Broadway, an adults-only evening of great food and drink, live music and silent auction.--also: it\'s SUPERHERO DAY!!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Thursday 27 November and Friday 28 November--no school Happy Thanksgiving to All!!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div id=\":19h\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ssl.gstatic.com/ui/v1/icons/mail/images/cleardot.gif\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Harvest Fest Thank Yous--Barnes and Noble Book Fair--Important Dates in November','','publish','open','open','','harvest-fest-thank-yous-barnes-and-noble-book-fair-and-other-news','','','2014-10-29 16:02:23','2014-10-29 20:02:23','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1434',0,'post','',0),(1698,1,'2014-11-17 12:01:44','2014-11-17 17:01:44','<div><strong>Thanks to the Wellness Committee-Tina, Lori, Karen, Trina and Rachel: CWS has been awarded a wellness grant for $2500 and our children have started getting physical education instruction from Keenan and Lee of PEP.</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>Thanks to Melissa for writing and winning a $1000 Love Your Block grant--we will use the money for tree guards around the trees in front of the school building.</strong></div>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SCRIP gift card orders are due Monday 24 November</span></strong>--each gift card gives a certain percentage to our PTA to fund programs like the CWS Band, Bent on Learning yoga, etc.  For example, get a <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">$100 Lands End gift card and $16 will go to the CWS PTA</span></strong>.  The gift cards are from ITunes, Barnes and Noble, Starbucks, Old Navy, Children\'s Place, etc.   Thanks to Tiffany and Beth for organizing.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Monday 24 November--6pm--Diversity Committee meeting-please email Luke luke.henry@gmail.com if you are able to attend</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday 24 November: GO Project applications due:  year-round academic support and family services for 1, 2, 3 graders. goprojectnyc.org</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Wishing all a wonderful and restful Thanksgiving break!  No school on 27 and 28 November.</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMonday 1 December--World AIDS Day-the whole school will join a community walk in Tompkins Square Park\r\n\r\nGet ready for the <strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Winter Craft Fair,</span></strong>---<strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Friday 5 December</span></strong>--all sorts of handmade lovely gifts from clothes to accessories to baked goods and candies to candles and home decor.  Thank you to Bari, Rosie and Keiko for organizing--contact Bari if you would like you sell your crafts (donate a percentage or all to the school): bari161@me.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1455\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/CRAFTFAIRSIGNUP14c-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"CRAFTFAIRSIGNUP14c\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Fri 5 December--drawing at Community Meeting for the <em>Nutcracker</em> raffle:  2 tickets to The Joffrey Ballet School\'s production of <em>The Nutcracker</em> at the NYU Skirball Center on Sat 14 Dec at 1pm. Thanks to Daryl and Sean for donating the tix!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">Round Two of the Barnes and Noble Book Fair will be 7-13 December (thank you, Nicole)!  Mark your calendars:  Victoria Kann will read from her  <em>Pinkalicious</em> series on Sunday 7 December at 2pm</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Original Works orders --the kids\' artwork made into holiday gifts like coffee mugs and tote bags--will arrive by 10 December. Thank you to Nicole for organizing.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008080;\">TUES 16 DECEMBER --PTA MEETING AFTER DROP OFF IN THE LOBBY</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Friday 19 December--Pajama Day! and the Hip Hop Club will perform at Community Meeting--plus drawing for 4 tickets to The Big Apple Circus\'s new show <em>Metamorphosis</em> on New Year\'s Day at 1pm!!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Holiday Break! No school from 24 December til 2 January--see you next year on Mon 5 January 2015!  Happy Healthy and Safe Holidays to All!!!</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFYI about After-school Clubs:  Fall clubs end 13 February. Spring club registration will be 10 Feb and 11 Feb from 8-9:30am in the lobby.  Spring clubs will begin 23 February!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1462\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/cws-dec-book-fair-14-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"cws dec book fair 14\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" />','Happy Thanksgiving and December News!  Winter Craft Fair! Barnes and Noble Book Fair Take 2!','','publish','open','open','','happy-thanksgiving-and-december-news-winter-craft-fair-barnes-and-noble-book-fair-take-2','','','2014-12-24 11:33:14','2014-12-24 16:33:14','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1454',0,'post','',0),(1476,1,'2014-11-28 00:34:22','2014-11-28 05:34:22','<a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1477\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1477\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/cwsfarmtripfundariser1.gif\" alt=\"cwsfarmtripfundariser\" width=\"380\" height=\"253\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEach year, the 4th grade class from the Children’s Workshop School in lower Manhattan takes a week-long trip to a working farm in New York’s Catskill Mountains.  For most of the children, not only is it their first time away from home, but it’s also their first time on a farm, surrounded by animals, fields, and nature.   They milk cows, watch lambs being born, and gather freshly laid eggs.  It is an amazing, enriching experience, fostering both independence and a connection to nature and farm work that not many children at public schools in New York City get to experience.  Thanks to a generous donation of many years standing, the children were able to go for five days.  Sadly, that annual $10,000 gift has ended, leaving Children’s Workshop with the prospect of a truncated 2-day farm trip for this year’s group of 4th graders.  We are hoping to make up that shortfall, but it’s a struggle for a small, progressive public school on the Lower East Side.  To that end, we are reaching out to family and friends, and their families and friends, to help us meet our goal.  Won’t you help us continue our school’s tradition?\r\n\r\nWe raised a whopping 75% of the goal of $10K to fund the farm trip for the 4th graders using the <a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\">GoFundMe site</a><a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\"> (http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo) </a>. Please spread the word! Every bit helps.','UPDATED! We raised 100% of the goal of $10,000 for the 4th Grade Farm Trip','','publish','open','open','','we-raised-75-of-the-goal-of-10000-for-the-4th-grade-farm-trip','','','2015-01-15 22:59:28','2015-01-16 03:59:28','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=1476',0,'post','',0),(1699,1,'2014-12-15 15:29:28','2014-12-15 20:29:28','<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Thank you to Nicole and our partners at Barnes and Noble--the December Barnes and Noble Book Fair to benefit our lovely CWS library was a great success---and round one in November netted $2700 for Dorothy to order books for the library (teachers and students provided their wish lists).</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Save your pennies, nickels, dimes and quarters for Change for Change--Elyssa\'s kindergarten and Scott\'s 5th grade classes are collecting change to donate to a cause to be determined.  Also--please save and bring in your Box Tops--put them in the Box Top container in front of Joyce\'s desk in the office.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008080;\">PTA Meeting--Tues 16 December at 8:45 in the lobby--help plan our evening PTA meeting on 20 January at 6pm!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Thurs 18 Dec at 6:30--EVCS invites CWS parents (no children) to attend their PA meeting presentation on diversity by Sally, CWS mom, co-chair of the CWS Diversity Committee and director of Teachers Unite!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>Friday 19 December:  Pajama Day!  Tiana\'s Hip Hop Club will perform at Community Meeting! Also at Community Meeting:  raffle drawing for 4 tickets to see The Big Apple Circus on New Year\'s Day--and raffle drawing for the Gigantic Basket Full of Kinetic Sand (bring the beach to your apartment!).  Tickets sold during Coffee And...Big Apple Circus tix are $2 each/3 for $5 and Kinetic Sand tix are $5 each/5 for $20.</