014-11-28 05:24:28','','4thgradefarmtrip2','','inherit','open','open','','4thgradefarmtrip2','','','2014-11-28 00:24:28','2014-11-28 05:24:28','',0,'http://cws.elab.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/4thgradefarmtrip2.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(1526,1,'2014-11-28 00:24:29','2014-11-28 05:24:29','','4thgradefarmtrip','','inherit','open','open','','4thgradefarmtrip','','','2014-11-28 00:24:29','2014-11-28 05:24:29','',0,'http://cws.elab.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/4thgradefarmtrip.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(1477,1,'2014-11-28 00:30:09','2014-11-28 05:30:09','','cwsfarmtripfundariser','','inherit','open','open','','cwsfarmtripfundariser-2','','','2014-11-28 00:30:09','2014-11-28 05:30:09','',0,'http://cws.elab.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/cwsfarmtripfundariser1.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(1651,1,'2012-10-29 16:14:44','2012-10-29 20:14:44','Mayor announced the Public Schools will be closed again tomorrow, Tuesday. Everyone, please be safe.','Closed again Tuesday','','publish','open','open','','closed-again-tuesday-3','','','2012-10-29 16:14:44','2012-10-29 20:14:44','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=628',0,'post','',0),(1788,1,'2014-12-24 11:32:16','2014-12-24 16:32:16','<a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1477\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1477\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/cwsfarmtripfundariser1.gif\" alt=\"cwsfarmtripfundariser\" width=\"380\" height=\"253\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEach year, the 4th grade class from the Children’s Workshop School in lower Manhattan takes a week-long trip to a working farm in New York’s Catskill Mountains.  For most of the children, not only is it their first time away from home, but it’s also their first time on a farm, surrounded by animals, fields, and nature.   They milk cows, watch lambs being born, and gather freshly laid eggs.  It is an amazing, enriching experience, fostering both independence and a connection to nature and farm work that not many children at public schools in New York City get to experience.  Thanks to a generous donation of many years standing, the children were able to go for five days.  Sadly, that annual $10,000 gift has ended, leaving Children’s Workshop with the prospect of a truncated 2-day farm trip for this year’s group of 4th graders.  We are hoping to make up that shortfall, but it’s a struggle for a small, progressive public school on the Lower East Side.  To that end, we are reaching out to family and friends, and their families and friends, to help us meet our goal.  Won’t you help us continue our school’s tradition?\r\n\r\nWe raised a whopping 75% of the goal of $10K to fund the farm trip for the 4th graders using the <a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\">GoFundMe site</a><a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo\"> (http://www.gofundme.com/h9pqgo) </a>. Please spread the word! Every bit helps.','We raised 75% of the goal of $10,000 for the 4th Grade Farm Trip','','inherit','open','open','','1476-revision-v1','','','2014-12-24 11:32:16','2014-12-24 16:32:16','',1476,'http://cws.elab.io/1476-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1789,1,'2014-12-24 11:33:14','2014-12-24 16:33:14','<div><strong>Thanks to the Wellness Committee-Tina, Lori, Karen, Trina and Rachel: CWS has been awarded a wellness grant for $2500 and our children have started getting physical education instruction from Keenan and Lee of PEP.</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>Thanks to Melissa for writing and winning a $1000 Love Your Block grant--we will use the money for tree guards around the trees in front of the school building.</strong></div>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SCRIP gift card orders are due Monday 24 November</span></strong>--each gift card gives a certain percentage to our PTA to fund programs like the CWS Band, Bent on Learning yoga, etc.  For example, get a <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">$100 Lands End gift card and $16 will go to the CWS PTA</span></strong>.  The gift cards are from ITunes, Barnes and Noble, Starbucks, Old Navy, Children\'s Place, etc.   Thanks to Tiffany and Beth for organizing.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Monday 24 November--6pm--Diversity Committee meeting-please email Luke luke.henry@gmail.com if you are able to attend</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday 24 November: GO Project applications due:  year-round academic support and family services for 1, 2, 3 graders. goprojectnyc.org</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Wishing all a wonderful and restful Thanksgiving break!  No school on 27 and 28 November.</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMonday 1 December--World AIDS Day-the whole school will join a community walk in Tompkins Square Park\r\n\r\nGet ready for the <strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Winter Craft Fair,</span></strong>---<strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Friday 5 December</span></strong>--all sorts of handmade lovely gifts from clothes to accessories to baked goods and candies to candles and home decor.  Thank you to Bari, Rosie and Keiko for organizing--contact Bari if you would like you sell your crafts (donate a percentage or all to the school): bari161@me.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1455\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/CRAFTFAIRSIGNUP14c-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"CRAFTFAIRSIGNUP14c\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Fri 5 December--drawing at Community Meeting for the <em>Nutcracker</em> raffle:  2 tickets to The Joffrey Ballet School\'s production of <em>The Nutcracker</em> at the NYU Skirball Center on Sat 14 Dec at 1pm. Thanks to Daryl and Sean for donating the tix!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">Round Two of the Barnes and Noble Book Fair will be 7-13 December (thank you, Nicole)!  Mark your calendars:  Victoria Kann will read from her  <em>Pinkalicious</em> series on Sunday 7 December at 2pm</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Original Works orders --the kids\' artwork made into holiday gifts like coffee mugs and tote bags--will arrive by 10 December. Thank you to Nicole for organizing.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #008080;\">TUES 16 DECEMBER --PTA MEETING AFTER DROP OFF IN THE LOBBY</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Friday 19 December--Pajama Day! and the Hip Hop Club will perform at Community Meeting--plus drawing for 4 tickets to The Big Apple Circus\'s new show <em>Metamorphosis</em> on New Year\'s Day at 1pm!!</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Holiday Break! No school from 24 December til 2 January--see you next year on Mon 5 January 2015!  Happy Healthy and Safe Holidays to All!!!</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFYI about After-school Clubs:  Fall clubs end 13 February. Spring club registration will be 10 Feb and 11 Feb from 8-9:30am in the lobby.  Spring clubs will begin 23 February!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1462\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/cws-dec-book-fair-14-231x300.jpg\" alt=\"cws dec book fair 14\" width=\"231\" height=\"300\" />','Happy Thanksgiving and December News!  Winter Craft Fair! Barnes and Noble Book Fair Take 2!','','inherit','open','open','','1698-revision-v1','','','2014-12-24 11:33:14','2014-12-24 16:33:14','',1698,'http://cws.elab.io/1698-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1790,1,'2014-12-24 12:01:01','2014-12-24 17:01:01','','bg5','','inherit','open','open','','bg5','','','2014-12-24 12:01:01','2014-12-24 17:01:01','',0,'http://cws.elab.io/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/bg5.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1834,1,'2015-02-09 00:48:10','2015-02-09 05:48:10','<a title=\"Supply List 2014-2015\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/schoolsupplylistCWSF2014.pdf\">Classroom Supply List 2014