WScraftfairposter2011\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/CWScraftfairposter2011.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"544\" /></a>','11/30/2011 CWS Holiday Crafts Fair is coming up!! Don\'t miss it!','','publish','open','open','','11302011-cws-holiday-crafts-fair-is-coming-up-dont-miss-it','','','2011-11-30 09:00:36','2011-11-30 09:00:36','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=167',0,'post','',0),(327,1,'2012-09-26 19:42:23','2012-09-26 19:42:23','<p align=\"center\">The Children’s Workshop School Update</p>\n<p align=\"center\">For the Weeks of 24 September and 1 and 8 October 2012</p>\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Museo-700\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\nWe’ve had a <strong>great kick-off to the school year</strong>, in spite of the construction: thank you to all families for attending the PTA Welcome Breakfast, the first PTA meeting, and Curriculum Night (thank you to parents/grandparents who volunteered to watch the kids).  We hope you got a lot of information out of these events.  If you have any further questions for your child’s teacher, please write a note and put it in your child’s backpack or in the teacher’s mailbox in the office and she/he will contact you.  For the safety of all the children, please don’t ask questions of your child’s teacher during arrival and dismissal as the teachers need to focus on their students.<!--more-->\n\nDorothy sent out <strong>middle school directories to all 5<sup>th</sup> grade families</strong>—any 5<sup>th</sup> grade family who did not receive one, please visit Dorothy in the library, call or email: <a href=\"mailto:dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov\">dcantwell2@schools.nyc.gov</a>\n\nThank you to Melissa, Heather and crew who are doing <strong>Coffee And…</strong> in front of the schoolyard entrance almost every Friday during drop-off and before Community Meeting.  If you can donate or help sell, email Melissa: Melissa@childrensworkshopschool.org\n\nKeiko is selling the Rosie-designed <strong>retro-cool CWS t-shirts</strong> (thanks, Rosie!) almost every Friday morning—be on the lookout for logo water bottles.  An anonymous friend of our school has also designed and donated another CWS logo t-shirt—we will be selling those soon (thank you!).  To help out Keiko out with t-shirt sales on Friday mornings, email Keiko: <a href=\"mailto:treasurer@childrensworkshopschool.org\">treasurer@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n<strong><em>WEEK OF 24 SEPTEMBER</em></strong>\n\n<strong>No school on Weds 26 September for Yom Kippur.</strong>\n\n<strong>Thurs 27 September</strong>-for women only:  Rachel, a Children’s Workshop School mom (also new Clubs Treasurer) and dancer, is leading <strong>a JourneyDance</strong> workshop at the Paul Taylor Dance Company,551 Grand Street at8pm—check the bulletin board in the lobby for full information.\n\n<strong>Friday 28 September:  Hagen Daz Scoops</strong>!—five mystery teachers will be scooping ice cream at the Hagen Daz on 8<sup>th</sup> Street west of Broadway from 4-7pm—half of the sales will go to our school.  Thanks to Melissa for organizing this fun fundraiser and to the teachers for volunteering to scoop.\n\n<strong><em>WEEK OF 1 OCTOBER</em></strong>\n\n<strong>Monday 1 October:  First day of clubs!</strong>  Thanks to Darryl, Rachel and Joyce for organizing such a wonderful selection of after-school clubs—and thanks to the club leaders, many of whom are parents or long-time friends of our school, for sharing their knowledge, talents and cultures with our children.\n\n<strong>Monday 1 October—CWS Library opens!</strong>  Dorothy thanks the PTA for funding a new computer system and the Library Committee parent volunteers, Holly and Margo, for helping her get our fantastic library ready for the new school year.  Contact Dorothy if you would like to volunteer one day a week.  She will also schedule a full day of book covering and will be looking for volunteers.\n\n<strong>Friday 5 October—Coffee And… and T-shirt sales</strong> during drop-off and before Community Meeting.\n\n<strong><em>WEEK OF 8 OCTOBER</em></strong>\n\n<strong>No school on Monday 8 October—Columbus Day</strong>\n\n<strong>Saturday 13 October:  Harvest Festival!</strong> 11-3 in the schoolyard, lobby, cafeteria and tar beach!  Bring friends and family as we celebrate the revival of a Children’s Workshop School tradition in honor of <strong>our school’s 20<sup>th</sup> anniversary and Maria’s 20<sup>th</sup> anniversary as principal</strong>.  There will be fall harvest class and family presentations and activities, delicious food representing the diverse cultures of our school community, and live music!  To help out (especially with set-up and clean-up), contact Julie <a href=\"mailto:co-vice-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-vice-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> or Elizabeth at <a href=\"mailto:co-president2@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-president2@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n<strong><em>LOOKING FORWARD:</em></strong>\n\nNext school year, our school building, named for doctor and activist Anna Howard Shaw, is turning 100 years old.  The three schools in the building, EVCS,  PS 94 and us, are organizing a celebration in early Fall 2013.  If you would like to get involved in researching and planning, please join the <strong>100 Year Celebration Committee</strong>—email Beth at <a href=\"mailto:co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n<strong>The next PTA meeting is Weds 24 October after drop-off in the lobby.</strong>\n\nCheck the school website at childrensworkshopschool.org, the bulletin board in the lobby and your child’s backpack for updates and information.  The school calendar on the website can be uploaded right into a smartphone.  If you have any items for this update sent via Dorothy’s list, email Beth at <a href=\"mailto:co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;','Weekly Updates Sept 24 ~ October 8','','publish','open','open','','weekly-update','','','2012-09-26 19:42:23','2012-09-26 19:42:23','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=327',0,'post','',0),(437,1,'2012-09-13 09:00:00','2012-09-13 09:00:00','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Fall12 Clubs List\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/FALL-clubs-list-2012-.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">\nPlease click here to download the list of Fall 2012 Clubs offered.</a></p>\nDear Parents,\nWelcome to a new session of after school clubs! Please take time to read this letter and the clubs list, as there is some new information. FALL SESSION REGISTRATION DATES: WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 19TH, AND THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 20TH. REGISTRATION WILL BE HELD IN THE LOBBY FROM 7:45AM TO 9:00am. FALL CLUBS BEGIN MONDAY, OCTOBER 1ST and will end Friday, February 22ND. There will be a registration for Spring clubs at the end of January and then Spring Clubs will start Monday, February 25TH and end FRIDAY, June 21ST.<img title=\"More...\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wordpress/img/trans.gif\" alt=\"\" /><!--more-->\n\nTHERE WILL BE NO BREAK IN BETWEEN FALL AND SPRING CLUBS.\n\nThis year, we will add an extra week onto each semester of clubs making each club last 17 weeks instead of 16 as in the past, in order to offer clubs earlier in October and later in June to accommodate busy parents. Because of that and increasing costs, all clubs will cost $230 for the 17 sessions which makes the cost for each session $12. Some clubs require a $10 or $20 materials fee. We will offer a 20% discount to those enrolling in 4 or more clubs. There will also be an option of picking up your child at 6pm if desired. See next page for more information on this. To cover the program’s expenses each club must have a minimum of 6 children enrolled per instructor.\n\nWe are also very pleased to announce that our school secretary, Joyce Borden, will be helping again with the clubs program and Rachael Frank, a CWS parent, has stepped up to replace Claudia Jungkunst,who’s daughter completed fifth grade and is no longer at the school. PLEASE FILL OUT ALL NECESSARY FORMS BEFORE COMING TO REGISTRATION. THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT! This will help the registration process move more quickly.\nMake checks payable to The CWS PTA. Also, credit cards may now be used as well. Please try to hand in completed forms and payment at registration. DO NOT HAND IN REGISTRATION FORMS TO THE OFFICE! There will be a lottery for clubs that are over enrolled so there is no need to worry about being first at registration. Parents may register for the children of ONE other family in addition to their own. So, if you are unable to make registration for whatever reason, you may ask another parent to register your children for you. A list of the clubs will be displayed at registration so parents will be able to see which clubs are full and which have spaces left. As ever, no one should hesitate to join a club for lack of money. If your family needs assistance, contact me or Maria Velez-Clarke. If you have any questions or concerns, you may contact me (917)482-7486 or DARRYLANDSCOTT@AOL.COM.\nSnack will be provided to all children right after school. However, since the school no longer qualifies for free lunch, it is the same with snack. We will still be able to get snack but there will be a small charge for it. Club kids will be required to pay this additional cost. We haven’t found out yet how much it will be but as soon as we find out we will ask all parents to pay for the snack. Parents or caretakers should pick up their children promptly at 4:45 in the lobby. Please be on time! Club leaders have to leave promptly at 4:45. You also have the option of putting your child in the <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">extended day option</a> and pick your child up any time between 4:45 and 6pm. Clubs do not meet on half days, school holidays, and parent teacher conference days.<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/EXTENDED-LETTER-FALL-2012.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> (Click here for detailed pricing for Extended Day&gt;&gt;).</a>\n\nSincerely,\nDarryl LaVare.\nParent and Clubs Administrator (mother of Jane in Susan’s class and Justine in Molly’s class).','Afterschool Clubs Registration','','publish','open','open','','afterschool-clubs-registration','','','2012-09-13 09:00:00','2012-09-13 09:00:00','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=437',0,'post','',0),(456,1,'2012-09-26 09:00:41','2012-09-26 09:00:41','If you have not filled out your lunch form please do so! All families must file one, even if you are not applying for school lunch. Just check the box on the top left. You can also fill out the form on line\n\n3rd 4th and 5th grade parents. If you have not signed on to ARIS, please contact me for your password.\n\n5th grade parents .. please touch base with me about your middle school search.\n\nYou can find me in the library~','Dorothy\'s Note','','publish','open','open','','dorothys-note','','','2012-09-26 09:00:41','2012-09-26 09:00:41','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=456',0,'post','',0),(523,1,'2012-10-09 09:00:25','2012-10-09 09:00:25','Thanks to all who are helping to organize the harvest festival which will be held rain or shine this Saturday, 13th of October.  Many families are making baked goods but we need more main-course dishes---honey-baked ham, pernil with rice and beans, mac and cheese, etc.  Also we need folding chairs, stools and tables---if you can contribute food or chairs/tables, Please let Julie and Elizabeth know:  <a href=\"mailto:ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.<wbr>org</wbr></a>\n\nplease spread the word-class parents:  please send out to your class list.\nthanks!\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/cwsharvestfestival2012.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-525\" title=\"Harvest Festival 2012\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/cwsharvestfestival2012.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"786\" /></a>','Harvest Festival this coming Saturday, the 13th','','publish','open','open','','harvest-festival-this-coming-saturday-the-13th','','','2012-10-09 09:00:25','2012-10-09 09:00:25','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=523',0,'post','',0),(535,1,'2012-10-04 09:00:03','2012-10-04 09:00:03','Everything is shaping up great for the harvest festival next Saturday, 13 Oct from 11-3\n\n--live music, arts and crafts, activities, dancing.  if you want to help, please gather in the lobby after drop off (which is also in the lobby today) for a quick meeting--look for Julie and Elizabeth.\n\nWe are looking forward to a fun day kicking off the year\'s celebrations of our school\'s and maria\'s 20th anniversary!','Harvest Festival Committee: Quick Meeting after Drop-Off Tomorrow, October 5','','publish','open','open','','quick-meeting-after-drop-off-tomorrow-october-5','','','2012-10-04 09:00:03','2012-10-04 09:00:03','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=535',0,'post','',0),(555,1,'2012-10-17 11:28:40','2012-10-17 15:28:40','Thank you for understanding and bearing the inconvenience of not having our Auditorium available for CWS Drop-off hours, as well as our Friday morning Community meetings. We have negotiated and are closely working with the DOE and contractors to prioritize the safety of the children. If you have any questions on the matter, please feel free to come to the office. Thank you!\n\nWe are going to document the demolition and construction of our beloved Auditorium each month.\n\nSeptember, 2012\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_546\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-1.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-546\" title=\"constructionSept2012-1\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-1-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> September 2012: First steps of the demolition in the auditorium.[/caption]</td>\n<td> <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-2.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-547\" title=\"constructionSept2012-2\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-2-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_550\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-5.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-550\" title=\"constructionSept2012-5\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-5-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Floor boards being carried out.[/caption]</td>\n<td>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_551\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"225\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-6.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-551\" title=\"constructionSept2012-6\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-6-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a> Working after-school hours into the night.[/caption]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_553\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-8.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-553\" title=\"constructionSept2012-8\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-8-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Ready for the truck[/caption]</td>\n<td>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_548\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-3.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-548\" title=\"constructionSept2012-3\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/constructionSept2012-3-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a> Where the stage used to be.[/caption]</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','Auditorium Demolition & Construction Updates','','publish','open','open','','auditorium-demolition-construction-updates','','','2012-10-17 11:28:40','2012-10-17 15:28:40','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=555',0,'post','',0),(566,1,'2012-10-17 14:39:14','2012-10-17 18:39:14','Hi, as a parent, I want to share with you a photo from a recent community meeting.  For those who don’t know, Community Meeting is a CWS tradition and it is held every Friday morning after drop-off.  Currently, we are meeting in the lobby.  Fellow parents, I encourage you to stay after drop-off on Friday mornings to hear the fun songs, see the happy faces of our children and teachers (especially Gary), and buy a snack or coffee from our weekly bake sale (CWS t-shirts and tote bags are also available).  As you can see here, our children and teachers refuse to let these temporary construction projects dampen their school spirit!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/despite-the-construction-community-meetings-go-happily-on/communitymeetinglobbyoct2012/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-567\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-567\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/CommunityMeetingLobbyOct2012-550x550.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"550\" /></a>\n\n(photo approved to post by Maria)','Despite the construction, Community Meetings go happily on~','','publish','open','open','','despite-the-construction-community-meetings-go-happily-on','','','2012-10-17 14:39:14','2012-10-17 18:39:14','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=566',0,'post','',0),(573,1,'2012-10-18 12:45:13','2012-10-18 16:45:13','With First Lady Michelle Obama’s Chefs Move to Schools &amp; Healthy Kids initiatives, CWS has a healthy lunch menu this year.\n\n<a title=\"October2012 Healthy Lunch Menu\" href=\"http://wellnessintheschools.org/images/Cook_Toolkit/oct%202012%20alternative%20menu%20final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here&gt;&gt; to download the October Menu PDF. Also available at Wellnessintheschools.org</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/healthy-bodies-healthy-minds-the-correct-october-lunch-menu/oct-2012-alternative-menu-final-xls-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-575\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-575\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/oct-2012-alternative-menu-final1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"736\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;','Healthy Bodies, Healthy Minds. The correct October Lunch Menu','','publish','open','open','','healthy-bodies-healthy-minds-the-correct-october-lunch-menu','','','2012-10-18 12:45:13','2012-10-18 16:45:13','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=573',0,'post','',0),(580,1,'2012-10-22 15:57:30','2012-10-22 19:57:30','<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Weeks of 22 and 29 October 2012</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\nElizabeth and Julie send out their <strong>thanks to all who volunteered for and attended the Harvest Festival!  It is wonderful the way our school community works together.  </strong>We had a fantastic fun day with <strong>250</strong> people in attendance and we raised over <strong>$3000</strong> for school programs and supplies. <strong>Special thanks to parents/grandparents/students/alumni:</strong> Judy, Rosie, Paul, John, Michelle, Sean, Holly, Lori, Gilda, Pier and Brook, Roxanne and Ken, Miriam, Sayoko, Tomo, Yuki, Irene, Nancy, Melissa, Michael and family for donating the square dance caller, Bryan and his band Filthy Rotten System, Scott, Kanwal and Nina, Jane and Justine, Rachel, Darryl, Leila and Bess, Irina, Annabel, Bari and Michelle, the farmer, Leslie, Tiffany, Khadejah, Hope, Holly…<strong>forgive us if we left your name out</strong>…<strong>Extra thanks to our teachers and staff</strong>:  Joyce, Gary, Dorothy,  Scott, Casey, Susan, Beverly, Kimberly, Elyssa, Miriam, Molly (with baby!), Maria (with grandchildren!); <strong>our custodial staff</strong>, Chris, Alicea, and Francesca; and <strong>our school safety officer</strong>, Officer Baptiste.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2060/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-592\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-592\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2060-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2045/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-591\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-591\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2045-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2032/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-590\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-590\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2032-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2025/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-589\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-589\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2025-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2021/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-586\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-586\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2021-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> <a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/580/dscn2160/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-587\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-587\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DSCN2160-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n<!--more-->\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe only casualty of Harvest Fest:  4<sup>th</sup> grader Frieda lost her pink scarf that she knitted herself—if you <strong>find Frieda’s pink scarf</strong>, please bring it to the Lost and Found in the office.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPaul and Justin will be coordinating the <strong>fundraising phone-a-thon</strong>---if you are able to volunteer an evening in early/mid November, email Paul at <a href=\"mailto:powernyc@hotmail.com\">powernyc@hotmail.com</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Penny Harvest</strong>—Elyssa’s kindergarten class and Michelle P.’s ½ class are coordinating this year’s Penny Harvest—bring bags of pennies and change to your child’s classroom—all the change gathered will be donated to those in need.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Check the school website often</strong>: <strong>childrensworkshopschool.org</strong>---newly redesigned by Keiko, Ian and the Tech Team with a constantly updated school calendar, lunch menus, and news.  <strong>Thank you Tech Team!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Ongoing thanks to Melissa, Heather, donators and crew for Coffee And... every Friday.  If you’d like to donate and/or help sell, email Melissa at </strong><a href=\"mailto:fundraising@childrensworkshopschool.org\"><strong>fundraising@childrensworkshopschool.org</strong></a><strong></strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Be sure to return school picture money to Joyce ASAP.</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>Be on the lookout at drop-off and pick-up here and there for the extended sales of the  <strong>50/50 raffle ($1 per chance) and the raffle of 2 tickets to see The Little Orchestra Society\'s production of <em>Babes in Toyland</em> at Lincoln Center </strong>on Saturday 8 Dec at 1:00pm ($1 per chance/8 chances for $5).  Raffle drawings will take place at a date TBA.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>The PTA meeting survey said...most families prefer morning meetings—October’s meeting is Weds 24 Oct after drop-off in the lobby</strong>. We will also have one evening meeting in May.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Week of 22 Oct:</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds 24 Oct:  PTA Meeting--after drop-off in the lobby.  Please make every effort to attend!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds 24 Oct:  District 1 Community Education Council (CEC) Meeting</strong>—6:00pm at PS 20, 166 Essex Street, corner of Houston St.  Childcare and light refreshments provided.   Discussion of the Common Core Curriculum changes and testing with the top DOE official and Chief Accountability Officer, Shael Suransky.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Thurs 25 Oct: Parent Workshop:  What Children Need to Succeed!</strong> with the always dynamic Early Childhood Social Worker for our school and EVCS, <strong>Valerie Preston--after drop-off in the lobby, coffee and bagels will be served.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Friday 26 Oct:  Pajama Day!</strong> Bring $2 in an envelope for the 5<sup>th</sup> grade Washington, DC trip fundraiser if your child participates by wearing his/her jammies to school.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Week of 29 Oct:</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Monday 29 Oct:  Picture Day!!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds 31 Oct:  Please remember The Children\'s Workshop School does not celebrate Halloween-please do not send your child to school in costume.  We hope everyone has a ton of fun celebrating a safe Halloween AFTER school!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Looking Forward: Mark Your Calendars!</span></strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Tues 6 November-Election Day-no school</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Monday 12 November-Veteran\'s Day-no school</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Tuesday 13 November--no clubs-evening conferences</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Weds 14 November-1/2 day (no clubs) afternoon conferences</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<strong> </strong>\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth at <a href=\"mailto:beth@childrensworkshopschool.org\">beth@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>','Bi-Weekly Updates','','publish','open','open','','580','','','2012-10-22 15:57:30','2012-10-22 19:57:30','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=580',0,'post','',0),(595,1,'2012-10-24 15:34:22','2012-10-24 19:34:22','Pajama day is coming up this Friday! It is a fundraiser hosted by our very own 5th Graders for their trip to Washington D.C. Please dress up in your pajamas- (over your clothes, or...dress appropriately over it so you won\'t catch a cold!) Please bring $2 and hand in to your teachers.\n\nWill your teacher come in his/her pajamas?\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/pajama-day-this-friday/pajamaday/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-596\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-596\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/pajamaday-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>','PAJAMA DAY!!! This Friday','','publish','open','open','','pajama-day-this-friday','','','2012-10-24 15:34:22','2012-10-24 19:34:22','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=595',0,'post','',0),(600,1,'2012-10-24 15:46:15','2012-10-24 19:46:15','Tonight- October 24, from 6pm at P.S. 20, Anna Silver School Auditorium (166 Essex Street) CHILDCARE provided.\n\nThe DOE\'s Deputy Chancellor for testing will present about the new tests and common core curriculum.  Please come to represent CWS!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?attachment_id=602\">To download the CEC meeting calendar please click here&gt;&gt;</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/district-1-cec-meeting-regarding-new-school-years-testing-teaching-learning-accountability/deputy-chancellor-shael-suransky/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-603\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-603\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/DEPUTY-CHANCELLOR-SHAEL-SURANSKY-550x646.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"646\" /></a>','District 1 CEC meeting regarding New School Year\'s Testing, Teaching, Learning & Accountability','','publish','open','open','','district-1-cec-meeting-regarding-new-school-years-testing-teaching-learning-accountability','','','2012-10-24 15:46:15','2012-10-24 19:46:15','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=600',0,'post','',0),(614,1,'2012-10-25 12:12:14','2012-10-25 16:12:14','Come and join Joyce in giving a tour of CWS to prospective parents.  8:45 ~ 10am. Meeting in the lobby.\n\nFuture dates are available on the <a title=\"CALENDAR\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/calendar/\">Calendar</a>, and on the <a title=\"School Tours\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/admissions/school-tours/\">Admissions page</a>.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/cws-school-tour-coming-up/microsoft-word-cws-open-house-flyer-fall-2012-doc/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-615\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-615\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/CWS-SchoolTour-Flyer-Fall-2012-550x704.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"704\" /></a>','CWS School Tour Coming up!','','publish','open','open','','cws-school-tour-coming-up','','','2012-10-25 12:12:14','2012-10-25 16:12:14','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=614',0,'post','',0),(624,1,'2012-10-30 21:00:50','2012-10-31 01:00:50','<strong>All NYC Public Schools </strong><strong>REMAIN CLOSED on Wednesday, 10/31/12</strong>\n\nPlease continue to monitor the news and <a href=\"http://www.nyc.gov/\">www.nyc.gov</a> for updates to the City\'s response to Hurricane Sandy.\n\n<hr />\n\n<div id=\"announcementItem\">\n\nSubscribe to receive notifications from NYC and the DOE:\n<a href=\"https://a858-nycnotify.nyc.gov/NotifyNYC/Enrollment/Default.aspx\"><img src=\"http://static3.echalk.net/www/ud00/3/3881a3cd91de40b9ab7a4773dc7b124a/Personal_Images/notifyNYC.gif\" alt=\"\" /></a>\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/Subscribe/default.htm\"><img src=\"http://static3.echalk.net/www/ud00/3/3881a3cd91de40b9ab7a4773dc7b124a/Personal_Images/NYCDOE.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"132\" /></a>\n\n</div>','All NYC Public Schools remain Closed on Wednesday, 10/31/2012','','publish','open','open','','oct31-school-closed','','','2012-10-30 21:00:50','2012-10-31 01:00:50','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=624',0,'post','',0),(626,1,'2012-10-28 20:00:42','2012-10-29 00:00:42','Due to Hurricane Sandy, Public Schools are closed Monday!','DOE: Public Schools Closed For Monday','','publish','open','open','','doe-public-schools-closed-for-monday','','','2012-10-28 20:00:42','2012-10-29 00:00:42','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=626',0,'post','',0),(722,1,'2012-11-01 09:00:22','2012-11-01 13:00:22','<strong>All NYC Public Schools </strong><strong>REMAIN CLOSED until Friday, 11/02/12</strong>\n\nPlease continue to monitor the news and <a href=\"http://www.nyc.gov/\">www.nyc.gov</a> for updates to the City\'s response to Opening the Public Schools on Monday, November 5.\n\n<hr />\n\n<div>\n\nSubscribe to receive notifications from NYC and the DOE:\n<a href=\"https://a858-nycnotify.nyc.gov/NotifyNYC/Enrollment/Default.aspx\"><img src=\"http://static3.echalk.net/www/ud00/3/3881a3cd91de40b9ab7a4773dc7b124a/Personal_Images/notifyNYC.gif\" alt=\"\" /></a>\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/Subscribe/default.htm\"><img src=\"http://static3.echalk.net/www/ud00/3/3881a3cd91de40b9ab7a4773dc7b124a/Personal_Images/NYCDOE.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"132\" /></a>\n\n</div>','All schools closed until Friday.','','publish','open','open','','all-schools-closed-until-friday','','','2012-11-01 09:00:22','2012-11-01 13:00:22','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=722',0,'post','',0),(725,1,'2012-11-03 19:44:17','2012-11-03 23:44:17','My internet access is unreliable, so I cannot guarantee a quick response to individual emails, but I will do my best to stay connected.\n\nInternet access at last! Hoping that this note finds you safe.\n\n<strong>AS OF NOW, CWS will be able to open Monday November 5th</strong> and has not appeared on the relocation list.\n\nOn Friday, the teachers had to report to another location, and met with Maria to plan the reopening so that children will feel secure and that there will be as little disruption in the school day as possible.\n\nWe are gathering a team of parent volunteers to assist with outreach to our school community to assess the needs that our families have and to find ways to support them during the recovery. If you can help on Monday, please let me know. If you are in a difficult position yourself, and require assistance, please send me an email.\n\nWe have been thinking of you and your families and are looking forward to coming together as a community to support each other during this difficult time.\n\nPlease continue to watch the news for updates, and check the DOE website <a href=\"http://www.schools.nyc.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">www.schools.nyc.gov</a>    and <a href=\"www.nyc.gov\">NYC government website</a> for the most current information.\n\nMy internet access is unreliable, so I cannot guarantee a quick response to individual emails, but I will do my best to stay connected.\n\nBest,\n\nDorothy','Most recent update from Dorothy','','publish','open','open','','most-recent-update-from-dorothy','','','2012-11-03 19:44:17','2012-11-03 23:44:17','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=725',0,'post','',0),(727,1,'2012-11-03 20:00:26','2012-11-04 00:00:26','<p style=\"text-align: right\">November 3, 2012</p>\nDear CWS Community,\n\nI hope that you and your families are and have been safe during Hurricane Sandy who landed on our shores as a super storm. My heart and thoughts go out to families and staff  in our community who have suffered and experienced loss and relocation.  The images of the devastation and loss suffered by people in lower Manhattan, the shores of our city and our neighboring state of New Jersey are haunting and earth shattering for me. How does one recover?  I can only say that we banded together after 9/11 and again together we will weather this storm.  Know that we are here to help and support each other in any way we can. Please don’t hesitate to reach out to us with your needs.\n\nThe lack of internet access, phone, and transportation made it very difficult to communicate accurate information to you in a timely manner. <strong>I apologize for that. </strong>As you may already know, from tuning in to our DOE website, school closing, opening and relocation status changed daily, sometimes hourly.  All of this to say that it has been a very frustrating and confusing time for me and the staff.\n\nOn Friday our staff was relocated to Brandeis High School where we were graciously accommodated, so that we could plan for our safe return to our school building or a relocation site.\n\n<strong>Happily our school is ready to open on Monday, November 5<sup>th</sup> </strong>with power, and water pumped out of our basement. Thanks to Mike our custodial staff and the contractors on the auditorium and window project.\n\nWe have a plan which will begin with a gathering and community meeting on Monday. The teachers will then return to classrooms with their students to prepare for the rest of the week and the transition of our kids back to school.\n\nReturning to regular school schedules may take time. We will need support from our parent body.  We ask your help in reaching out to families who may be in need at this time.  We also ask your help in welcoming students and their families who may have been displaced and relocated to our school until they can safely return to their homes.\n\nOn Tuesday, students will be out of school again for Election Day. Our staff will be at school planning and working on next steps.\n\nBe Well and hope to see you all on Monday, November 5<sup>th</sup>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPeace\n\nMaria','Maria\'s Letter','','publish','open','open','','marias-letter','','','2012-11-03 20:00:26','2012-11-04 00:00:26','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=727',0,'post','',0),(732,1,'2012-11-04 18:40:05','2012-11-04 23:40:05','Message from PTA- Clubs resume tomorrow afternoon as well! See you all tomorrow!','There will be Clubs tomorrow, Monday, November 5','','publish','open','open','','there-will-be-clubs-tomorrow-monday-november-5','','','2012-11-04 18:40:05','2012-11-04 23:40:05','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=732',0,'post','',0),(735,1,'2012-11-09 12:16:15','2012-11-09 17:16:15','Below are important temporary phone numbers provided by the DOE while the phone lines are still down. 347-675-9415, and 347-675-9376.\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/temporary-cws-phone-number/emergencyphone/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-736\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-736\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/EmergencyPhone.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"584\" /></a>','Temporary CWS Phone Number','','publish','open','open','','temporary-cws-phone-number','','','2012-11-09 12:16:15','2012-11-09 17:16:15','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=735',0,'post','',0),(741,1,'2012-11-09 09:00:41','2012-11-09 14:00:41','We are all one family under one sky!\n\n<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/fundraising-at-matildas/matildalogo/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-742\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-742\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/matildalogo.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"77\" /></a>\n\nHurrican Sandy hammered local businesses in the East Village, including Matilda\'s, owned and operated by CWS family. Located on 11th street and Avenue C, their basement and refrigerator were flooded by the tidal surge and destroyed. Coupled with the power loss, they are in a very precarious financial situation along with every other restaurant and business in the flood zone. And yet, they were providing warm meals to shelters in the neighborhood.\n\nTo help them out, we are holding a fundraiser at Matilda\'s (647 East 11th Street) on Friday, November 16 from 4pm - 6pm. A Suggested $20 donation per person at the door will include a drink and appetizers. There will also be a donation box for those who wish to donate more. Please stop by, have a meal, and support our CWS families.\n\nThank you.\n\n--Fundraising Committee','Fundraising at Matilda\'s','','publish','open','open','','fundraising-at-matildas','','','2012-11-09 09:00:41','2012-11-09 14:00:41','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=741',0,'post','',0),(752,1,'2012-11-13 17:49:24','2012-11-13 22:49:24','Hello to 5th grade families... For updates about middle school, please <a title=\"Middle School Information\" href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/middle-school-information/\">click here&gt;&gt; </a>\n\n&nbsp;','Middle School Updates','','publish','open','open','','middle-school-updates','','','2012-11-13 17:49:24','2012-11-13 22:49:24','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=752',0,'post','',0),(756,1,'2012-11-14 11:24:15','2012-11-14 16:24:15','<p align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">CONSTRUCTION, BUILDING AND SAFETY UPDATE</span></strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></p>\nDear CWS Families:\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThank you all for your continued patience and understanding during all the various construction projects occurring both in and around our school building.  The following is a summarized status update concerning the various construction projects and issues related to those projects.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">EAST SIDE</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> COMMUNITY HIGH SCHOOL</span></strong><strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nAs most of you know the building housing East SideCommunityHigh Schooland Girls Prep, on E 12th between Ave A and 1st Ave, has been evacuated and is under construction because the building is compromised. The children attending those schools were evacuated within a two-hour window and they are now attending classes in other school buildings without most of their books and supplies—to help, see ESCHS’s website:   <a href=\"http://www.eschs.org/\">http://www.eschs.org/</a>.  The construction projects at our school building are not affected:  we meet weekly with the school construction authority and we have been assured that our building projects are staying on schedule.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">AUDITORIUM</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nWe have heard that, so far, there are no structural defects in the foundation under the auditorium.  This means that the project could be completed as early as April 2013!  (Worst case estimates are July 2013).  We have secured a $250,000 grant for light, sound and video for the new auditorium.  The Auditorium Committee, headed by Dorothy and comprised of parents with expertise in lighting, etc (Frank, Scott, Ken and Bill) will work with EVCS and PS94 to create a wonderful new system.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">CAMPOS</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> RECREATION SPACE</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nAll three schools have agreed to a schedule for our shared use of the Campos Gym/Auditorium Space on E 13th between Aves B and C.  Insurance coverage was also extended to the outdoor basketball courts.  The last piece to securing this space is security, which is currently in the works.  The space will be used throughout the school day but will not be used for recess, drop-off, pick-up or community meeting. However, these plans are on hold sinceCampossuffered damage from the hurricane.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">RECESS</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nAlthough our yard is diminished, we are still using it for recess.  During inclement weather, the children go to various locations in the building such as classrooms and the lobby where they can choose various activities such as art and board games.  Please be assured that we are making every effort to provide outdoor recess as much as possible.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">BRICK AND WINDOW REPLACEMENT</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nAs you can see our building is surrounded by scaffolding and we have lost a large portion of the school yard.  Our landmarked school building turns 100 years old this spring and these repairs must be done.  The project is scheduled to last until Spring 2014.  All of the bricks will be removed and replaced, and the building will be waterproofed.  In addition all of the windows will be replaced.  The good news is that the building is going to look amazing, it will no longer leak and our children will be able to see out of the windows!  We are hoping to get air conditioners into the second floor classrooms during or immediately after this project.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">189 AVENUE B BUILDING CONSTRUCTION</span></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> </span></strong>\n\nThe General Contractor for this project has been regularly communicating with our school regarding the schedule and progress of this project.  They received their foundation permit and that work started on Monday, October 22.  The first phase will be noisy as they shore up the soil and drive in piles to support the foundation.  They anticipate this phase will take approximately four weeks with only a handful of those days being noisy.  The work is being done under a required noise mitigation plan which was submitted to the Department of Education.  The next phase will be excavation and utility hookups.  The final phase will be the pouring of the foundation.  The GC is in talks with the developer about widening the sidewalk bridge at the corner and mitigating the water that is collecting in the gutter.  In addition, some of you have expressed concerns regarding soil, debris and noise coming from the building site.  The GC is also speaking with the project’s environmental consultant to get us answers as soon as possible.  The building project is supposed to be completed by February 2014.  The Developer has promised that our school will be given access to the community space that will occupy the ground floor.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">HURRICANE</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> SANDY BUILDING</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"> CLEAN-UP</span></strong>\n\nWe extend our gratitude to the auditorium and building façade construction crews, who were the first to respond to the flooding in our building basement, and to our building custodial staff and kitchen staff, who worked long hours over the weekend to ensure that the children returned to a clean and safe environment.  On 2 November, the air and water were tested and deemed safe.  As a precaution, the custodians ran all faucets to clear the pipes.  The kitchen staff completely cleared out and sanitized the kitchen, which passed inspection to re-open.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">REQUEST FOR ADDITIONAL SAFETY AGENT AND CROSSING GUARDS</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe principals of all three schools have requested an additional school safety agent and extended hours/personnel for safe crossing.  <strong>Please sign the petition to express your concern regarding the safety of our children!</strong> Parent volunteers will circulate the petition at drop-off and pick-up and you can also come to the office to sign.\n\n&nbsp;','Construction, Building and Safety Update','','publish','open','open','','construction-building-and-safety-update','','','2012-11-14 11:24:15','2012-11-14 16:24:15','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=756',0,'post','',0),(758,1,'2012-11-14 11:29:32','2012-11-14 16:29:32','<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Weeks of 12, 19 &amp; 26 November 2012</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\"></p>\n<strong>Hurricane Sandy Relief for Our Community (and Beyond)</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nThank you to everyone in our school community  for cooking up <strong>Stone Soup for the CWS Soul Masquerade Fun</strong>, making the children feel warm and welcome as they returned to school last week!  Both the PTA and the teachers are now cooking up hurricane relief efforts—we hope to see you at the <strong>Matilda fundraiser (16 Nov from 4-6)</strong> and be on the lookout for more announcements in backpacks and on the school website.  The kick-off event for the teacher/classroom fundraisers will be on Fri 16 Nov in the afternoon—a <strong>Pizza-Eating Contest!</strong>  Who can eat the most pizza: Scott, Jeff, Luis, Jason or Michelle M.?!\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIn the meantime, since <strong>each class will be putting together care packages</strong> for our neighbors at Campos Plaza and Haven Plaza, please gather up toiletries, diapers, wipes, cleaning supplies and other practical health and home care items to donate.   Remember to bring in your change for <strong>Penny Harvest</strong>—all Penny Harvest funds will be donated to hurricane relief.  Also, we will donate the proceeds from <strong>Original Works</strong> (the art fundraiser—your child’s art on coffee mugs, magnets, etc) to hurricane relief for our school community.  Thanks to Jennifer for coordinating Original Works every year.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf your family is in need of any hurricane relief assistance, please do not hesitate to tell Maria, Dorothy, Joyce, Sonia or your child’s teacher or class parent or PTA board member (ptaeb@childrensworkshopschool.org).  Know that our school social workers, Valerie (pre-k/k) and Aurora (1-5), are available for all families.  <strong>Lunch is free for the month of November and breakfast, which starts at 8am in the cafeteria, is always free and available for all children</strong>.  The Department of Education has not yet decided how the missed school days will be made up.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Other News:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe PTA phone drive has been postponed until after the New Year.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nContact Bari if you’d like to help out or sell your arts and crafts at the Holiday Craft Fair on Friday 7 Dec:  bari161@me.com\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSchoolapalooza—contact Ian  <a href=\"mailto:ian@childrensworkshopschool.org\">ian@childrensworkshopschool.org</a> to get involved with organizing our school’s major fundraiser event.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Sign the petition for another school security guard and increased crossing guard hours—in the office or look for Hope and her team gathering signatures at drop-off and pick-up.  Email Hope to help out: hbaker1@nyc.rr.com.</strong>  Maria, Robin from EVCS and Ronnie from PS94 are working on this with the Department of Education and the 9<sup>th</sup> Precinct.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Week of 12 November:</span></strong>\n\nMon 12 November: no school—Veteran’s Day\n\nTues 13 November:  evening conferences-no afterschool clubs\n\nWeds 14 November:  half day-11:30 dismissal—afternoon conferences-no clubs\n\nFri 16 November: Pizza-Eating Contest!—details to follow\n\n<strong>  16 Nov: Fundraiser for/at Matilda—11 St and Ave C—4-6pm—drinks and appetizers--$20 per person—children welcome!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Week of 19 November:</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds 21 Nov:  PTA meeting in cafeteria after drop-off</strong>\n\nThurs 22 Nov:  Thanksgiving-no school—enjoy!\n\nFri 23 Nov:  Thanksgiving Break-no school\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Week of 26 November:</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThurs 29 November:  picture day!\n\nFriday 30 November:  Fancy Dress Day!—also raffle tix sold and raffle drawing for <strong>50/50 raffle ($1 per chance) and the raffle of 2 tickets to see The Little Orchestra Society\'s production of <em>Babes in Toyland</em> at Lincoln Center </strong>on Saturday 8 Dec at 1:00pm ($1 per chance/8 chances for $5).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Looking Forward!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSaturday, 1 December:  A <strong>Baruch College professor and her students will lead a healthy foods workshop for kids and help with covering and shelving books in the library</strong>—be on the lookout for details in backpacks!  Thanks to Melissa for coordinating this event.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Friday, 7 December:  Holiday Craft Fair</strong>—do some holiday shopping for those on your list!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds, 19 December—PTA meeting after drop-off in the lobby</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nFri 21 Dec:  Twin/Triplet Day\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Holiday Break—No school from 24 Dec to 1 January—return to school on Weds 2 Jan!</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Congrats to David Riker</strong>, dad of Leila (Jessica’s class) and Maria (Susan’s class) and husband of Elizabeth, our PTA co-president:  his film <em>The Girl</em>, which had its New York premiere at the Tribeca Film Festival this past April, will be shown at the Landmark Sunshine Cinema on Houston St in March!\n\nOur clubs treasurer, Rachel, will be doing two <strong>JourneyDance workshops</strong>--one for women only and the other for couples--look for the announcement on the bulliten board in the lobby or email her: rachiefrank515@yahoo.com\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth: <a href=\"mailto:co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nRemember to check the school website regularly:  childrensworkshopschool.org\n\n&nbsp;','CWS Update for Weeks of 12, 19 and 26 November 2012','','publish','open','open','','cws-update-for-weeks-of-12-19-and-26-november-2012','','','2012-11-14 11:29:32','2012-11-14 16:29:32','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=758',0,'post','',0),(762,1,'2012-11-23 06:37:25','2012-11-23 11:37:25','Dear Families:\n\nWe are midway through our Penny Harvest.  So far, we have collected four full penny sacks, which is about 120 pounds of change!  Thank you for harvesting your change and bringing it in for us to donate.  This year, Penny Harvest has announced that 100% of the money will be donated to Hurricane Sandy relief organizations.  For more information, please visit www.commoncents.org.\n\nPlease continue to collect your change and bring it into school!  You can also ask friends and family to donate change as well.  We will send out a letter letting families know when the last day of Penny Harvest is.  Until then, happy harvesting and remember--every penny counts!\n\nFondly,\n\nThe Penny Harvest Leaders in Elyssa\'s class and Michelle F.\'s class\n\nHAPPY THANKSGIVING BREAK TO ALL!!!\n\nFrom the NYC DOE:  All schools will hold full-day sessions on Weds 20 Feb, Thurs 21 Feb, Fri 22 Feb and Tues 4 June to make up the learning time students missed due to Hurricane Sandy.  Mark your calendars!\n\n&nbsp;','Penny Harvest / Hurricane Sandy Make-Up Days','','publish','open','open','','penny-harvest-hurricane-sandy-make-up-days','','','2012-11-23 06:37:25','2012-11-23 11:37:25','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=762',0,'post','',0),(765,1,'2012-12-07 12:40:59','2012-12-07 17:40:59','Due to Hurricane Sandy, the school office landline is still not in service. Please use the temporary cell phone numbers to reach Joyce, Dorothy or Maria: 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376.','Temporary office phone numbers still in effect: 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376','','publish','open','open','','temporary-office-phone-numbers-still-in-effect-347-675-9415-or-347-675-936','','','2012-12-07 12:40:59','2012-12-07 17:40:59','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=765',0,'post','',0),(769,1,'2012-12-09 16:57:28','2012-12-09 21:57:28','<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Month of December 2012</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">temporary phone numbers:  347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376</p>\n<p align=\"center\">“We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<p align=\"center\"></p>\nThe pizza eating contest raised <strong>$544</strong> for hurricane relief!  Congrats and a vat of Tums to Jeff for eating a whole pizza pie.  Keep that change coming in for <strong>Penny Harvest</strong>-all funds raised will go to hurricane relief. <strong> Each class is gathering diapers, wipes, cleaning supplies, school supplies, etc to donate to Save the Children\'s Hurricane Sandy relief and will run bake sales--3rd and 4th grade classes will hold a bake sale on Friday 14 December and the 1/2 and 5th grade classes will hold theirs on Thurs 20 Dec--with all proceeds to go to Save the Children.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Thanks to all who attended the sangria-soaked fundraiser for Matilda</strong>—Maristella, Esteban and Matilda have been able to repair the walk-in refrigerator and send their appreciation out to our school community.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe <strong>charge of the Lice Brigade</strong> has begun—Nancy has done a great job coordinating the lice checks, along with help from Lori, Dafna and Judy. Remember, lice is a common nuisance among school-aged kids—there is no shame in having lice, just a big hassle!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Schoolapalooza planning is beginning</strong>: it’s the Children’s Workshop School’s major fundraiser, and adult-only evening in March of delicious food, silent auction, and great entertainment-made extra special this year because <strong>Maria and the school are celebrating our twentieth year anniversary.  Thanks to Ian, who will continue to be chair, Kim and Rachel, who have volunteered to be co-co-chairs with help from Lori,  and Nancy and Cassie, who will continue to coordinate the auction. To get involved, email Ian: ian@childrensworkshopschool.org</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPlease be sure to do some <strong>holiday shopping and support our school at the Winter Craft Fair</strong> <strong>on 7 Dec</strong>:  handmade jewelry, scarves, toys, cookies, jams and more will be for sale at prices ranging from $1 to $100. <strong>Thanks to Bari, Keiko, and Rosie for organizing the craft fair</strong> and to  the artisans and bakers for creating such beautiful items!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>SCRIP gift card forms have gone out in backpacks (due 10 December)</strong>---stores participating in the SCRIP program donate a percentage of the gift card amount to our school, anywhere from 1% to 18%.<strong>  Participating companies/stores include Starbucks, Barnes and Noble and Children’s Place.  You will receive your gift cards in time for holiday gift-giving</strong>.  Stock up on the Barnes and Noble gift cards if you can, to use when we have the Book Fair to benefit our school library at Barnes and Noble in February.   <strong>Thanks to Helen, Tiffany and Kanwal for coordinating the SCRIP program.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 3 December:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nMon, 3 Dec:  <strong>Lice check</strong>—Professonial Lice Manager Shayna Brown and her team will check every child’s head for lice.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThurs 6 December—Shayna Brown will do a <strong>lice comb-out demonstration for parents and caregivers after drop-off, and will give tips for preventing lice.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Fri 7 December—Winter Craft Fair—all day in the lobby, from drop-off to pick-up.  </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 10 December: </strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Mon 10 Dec:  SCRIP gift card orders are due!</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nTues 11 Dec:  Schoolapalooza planning meeting—in lobby after drop-off\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWeds 12 Dec:  PTA Executive Board meeting after drop-off in the library conference room\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Fri 14 Dec:  Bake sale organized by 3rd and 4th grade classes to benefit Save the Children Hurricane Sandy relief efforts. </strong> SLT (School Leadership Team) meeting at 7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 17 December:</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Weds 19 Dec:  PTA meeting after drop-off in the lobby</strong>\n\n<strong> Thurs, 20 Dec:  Bake sale organized by 1/2 and 5th grade classes to benefit Save the Children Hurricane Sandy relief funds.</strong>\n\nFri 21 Dec:  Twin/Triplet Day--$2 to benefit the fifth grader’s trip to Washington, DC\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Looking Forward!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Holiday Break—No school from 24 Dec to 1 January—return to school on Weds 2 Jan!</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Weds 16 January:  PTA meeting after drop-off in the cafeteria</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nThe event with Baruch College students leading a Healthy Eating Workshop and covering books in the library will be rescheduled in the Spring.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Happy Holidays to everyone in our school community and best wishes for a wonderful New Year.  Peace, love and a good rest to all!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth: <a href=\"mailto:co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\">co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p align=\"center\">Remember to check the school website regularly:</p>\n<p align=\"center\"> childrensworkshopschool.org</p>\n<p align=\"center\">“We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<p align=\"center\"></p>','CWS Update for the Month of December 2012','','publish','open','open','','cws-update-for-the-month-of-december-2012','','','2012-12-09 16:57:28','2012-12-09 21:57:28','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=769',0,'post','',0),(775,1,'2013-01-09 12:18:12','2013-01-09 17:18:12','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong>\n<strong>For January 2013</strong>\nhttp://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\ntemporary phone numbers: 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376\n”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>Happy New Year and welcome back to all!</strong></p>\n<strong>$4400 was raised at the Winter Craft Fair and Bake Sale!</strong>—thank you to Bari, Rosie, Keiko and all who volunteered to help set-up, sell and break-down the craft fair. Thanks as always to Melissa, Natalie, Heather and crew for running the Friday bake sales which are such an important part of our school community, the perfect accompaniment to Friday Community Meetings.\n\n<strong>Beverly’s “Making Creativity” and Jessica’s “Getting Movement in Our Day” projects both received funding through donorschoice.org</strong>—thanks to those families who donated and thanks to Donor’s Choice for matching the funds.\n\n<strong>Thank you to pre-k social worker Valerie</strong> for her workshop before the break about helping children cope with traumatic events. For continued support, do not hesitate to contact Valerie or Aurora—and also see the list of resources to support children in dealing with grief, loss and safety from the DOE: http://schools.nyc.gov/Offices/OSYD/Resources+to+Support+Children-.htm\n\n<strong>Schoolapalooza!!</strong>—contact Schoolapalooza chair Ian ian@childrensworkshopschool.org to get involved with organizing our school’s major fundraiser event—a night of fantastic food, drink, silent auction, and entertainment—this year celebrating our school’s 20th anniversary. Thanks to Kim, Rachel, Lori, Rina, Nancy and Cassie for forming the core of the committee.\n\nBe on the look-out for your child(ren)’s<strong> Original Works artwork order form</strong>—order coffee mugs, t-shirts, magnets, etc. All proceeds go to our school. Thanks to Jen for coordinating the Original Works fundraiser.\n<strong>Week of 7 January:</strong>\n\nFriday, 11 January: SLT meeting in Suma’s classroom at 7:30\n\n<strong>Week of 14 January:</strong>\n\n<strong>Wednesday, 16 January: PTA meeting in the cafeteria right after drop-off</strong>\n\nFriday 18 January: Fundraiser Phoneathon—thanks to Paul, Justin, and John for running the phoneathon.\n\n<strong>Week of 21 January:</strong>\n\n<em><strong>Monday, 21 January: Martin Luther King Day—no school</strong></em>\n\nTuesday, 22 January: Original Works order forms due./phoneathon continues\n\n<em><strong>Thursday 24 January: Martin Luther King Honoring the Dream Celebration—6pm at ICE/High School for Health Professions on 15th Street between 1st and 2nd Avenues. Every class will perform!</strong></em>\n\n<em><strong>Friday, 25 January: 1950s Day! and half day—12:10 dismissal—teachers will be going on their annual retreat</strong></em>\n\n<strong>Week of 28 January:</strong>\n\nMonday 28 January: Lice check! Thanks to Nancy, Judy, Dafna and Lori for coordinating and helping out.\n<strong>Looking Forward!</strong>\n\n<strong>Spring Clubs</strong> <strong>registration will be Weds 6 Feb and Thurs 7 Feb from 7:45-9am--be on the lookout for a club packet in backpacks.</strong> Remember, if any club is overbooked, it will go to a lottery—so there is no need to rush to be first in line to register. It’s a good idea to have a second choice for each club. <strong>Spring clubs will start Monday 25 February and run until Friday 21 June. There is no break between Fall clubs and Spring clubs.</strong> Some fun new clubs to look forward to: Multicultural Cooking Club, Mural Club, Fairytale Theater Club—and old favorites will be continuing: Guitar Club, Circus Club, Chess Club, Sports Club…etc etc! Thanks to Darryl, Rachel and Joyce for running the clubs and thanks to all the club leaders for providing our children with such fun and rich experiences.\n\n<strong>The Library Book Fair at Barnes and Noble will be in mid-February</strong>—be on the lookout for dates. Thanks to Carol, our retired librarian, who continues to coordinate the Book Fair for us every year!\n\n<strong>Terry, our music teacher, is a jazz singer and will be performing for free</strong> at Turtle Bay Music School, 244 East 52nd Street, on Friday 18 February at 7pm.\n\n<strong>Save the date: 7 June 2014—the 101 Year Celebration</strong>—our school building is 100 years old this year but we will be celebrating after the scaffolding is down with a huge block party in collaboration with East Village Community School and PS94.\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth:\n\nco-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org\n\nRemember to check the school website regularly: childrensworkshopschool.org\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">The Children’s Workshop School\nhttp://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\ntemporary phone numbers: 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376\n”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n&nbsp;','Children\'s Workshop School Update for January 2013','','publish','open','open','','childrens-workshop-school-update-for-january-2013','','','2013-01-09 12:18:12','2013-01-09 17:18:12','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=775',0,'post','',0),(781,1,'2013-02-05 11:33:58','2013-02-05 16:33:58','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong>\n<strong>For the Month of February 2013</strong>\n<strong>http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</strong>\n<strong>phone numbers:212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376</strong>\n<strong>”We’re all a family under one sky!”</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/25-jan-2013-017-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n<strong>Thank you and bravo! to our children and teachers for a wonderful and moving Honoring the Dream Celebration! </strong>Thanks to Scott for the sound, David H. for designing the fantastic poster, the High School for Health Professions/ICE for donating their huge auditorium, and all who stayed to help clean up.</p>\n<strong>Thank you to Melissa, grant-writer extraordinaire, for securing $5000 from Lowe’s Home Improvement Stores—we will use the funds for Imagination Playground foam blocks and tinker toy shapes (the exact same equipment as at the Imagination Playground at the Seaport but here, on our own school play-yard!).</strong> If you have grant-writing skills and want to help Melissa with researching and writing grants, email her: melissa.vigilante@dialog.com\n\n<strong>Schoolapalooza!!—We have a date; we have a location: Friday 12 April at the Clemente Soto Velez Center on the corner of Suffolk and Rivington Streets.</strong> Contact Schoolapalooza chair Ian ian@childrensworkshopschool.org to get involved with organizing our school’s major fundraiser event—a night of fantastic food, drink, silent auction, and entertainment—this year celebrating our school’s 20th anniversary. Thanks to Kim, Rachel, Lori, Rina, Nancy, Evan, Rodrigo and Cassie for forming the core of the committee.<strong> Every family can help by soliciting auction items—see the directions and forms sent home in backpacks. Extra copies are available in the office in the PTA mailbox.</strong>\n\nTechnology Team News:<strong> The $110,000 Reso-A Grant given to us through Councilwoman Rosie Mendez’s office will allow us to have Smartboards in every first through fifth grade classroom and new laptops for each grade.</strong> Installation should begin this Spring. The Tech Team (made up of Maria and Dorothy, teachers Susan, Scott, Crystal and Jessica; and parents Ian and Keiko) is also<strong> looking for a parent familiar with wordpress who can help with the aesthetics of our school website—please email: cwstechteam@gmail.com</strong>\n\n<strong>Activism News:</strong> The Gymnasium Committee, chaired by Dorothy, has begun to meet with EVCS and PS94 to form a strategy to build a gym. Thanks to Hope, Nancy, Rachel, Melissa, and Dorothy for getting the word out about the Town Hall meeting with Chancellor Walcott—and much appreciation to those families who were able to attend!\n\nThank you to those who volunteered their time to make calls for the<strong> Phoneathon</strong>: Justin, Paul, Francesca, Elizabeth, Michele, Margo, Tiffany, Keiko, Chris and John and thanks to those families who contributed.\n\n<strong>Friday Bake Sale—now selling books too!</strong> Please donate books (in good condition) and buy books—kids’ and adult books--$1 for hardcovers 50 cents for paperbacks. Thank you to Melissa, Heather, Natalie, Roxanne, Paul and everyone who contributes to and buys from our Friday bake/book sales.\n<strong>Week of 4 February:</strong>\n\nWeds 6 Feb: PTA Executive Board meeting after drop-off in library conference room\n\nWeds 6 Feb and Thurs 7 Feb: Spring clubs registration from 7:45-9am. Remember, if any club is overbooked, it will go to a lottery—so there is no need to rush to be first in line to register. Please have club forms filled out before you come to register.\n\nFriday 8 Feb: SLT meeting in Suma’s classroom at 7:30am\n\n<strong>Week of 11 February:</strong>\n\nWednesday, 13 February: PTA meeting in the lobby right after drop-off\n\nFriday 15 Feb: Monochromatic Day\n\n<strong>Week of 18 February: LAST WEEK OF FALL CLUBS</strong>\n\nMonday 18 Feb and Tues 19 Feb: No school “Winter Break”\n\nWeds 21 Feb: Lice check. Thanks to Nancy for coordinating and Lori, Dafna and Judy for helping out.\n\n<strong>Week of 25 February:FIRST WEEK OF SPRING CLUBS</strong>\nSpring clubs will start Monday 25 February and run until Friday 21 June. There is no break between Fall clubs and Spring clubs. Thanks to Darryl, Rachel and Joyce for running the clubs and thanks to all the club leaders for providing our children with such fun and rich experiences.\n\n<strong>Looking Forward!</strong>\n\nFamily conferences: afternoon conferences on Tues 12 March (1/2 day-clubs will not meet) and evening conferences on Weds 13 March (clubs will not meet)\n\nMarch PTA Meeting: 20 March after drop-off in the cafeteria\n\nSpring Break!: 23 March to 2 April—back to school Weds 3 April\n\nThe fourth graders’ farm trip is in April and the fifth graders are looking forward to their visit to Washington, DC in May.\n\n<strong>David R’s film, \"The Girl\" will open in theaters March 8th, International Women\'s Day, at the AMC Loews Theater on Third Ave and 11th Street and the Elinor Bunin Munroe Film Center at Lincoln Center.</strong> You can see a trailer and showtimes at: http://davidrikersthegirl.com\n\nSave the date: <strong>7 June 2014—the 101 Year Celebration</strong>—our school building is 100 years old this year but we will be celebrating after the scaffolding is down with a huge block party in collaboration with EVCS and PS94.\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth: co-president1@childrensworkshopschool.org<a href=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/the-childrens-workshop-school-update-for-february-2013/25-jan-2013-017/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-782\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-782 aligncenter\" src=\"http://childrensworkshopschool.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/25-jan-2013-017-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\">The Children’s Workshop School\nhttp://www.childrensworkshopschool.org\nphone numbers: 212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376\n”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"></p>','The Children\'s Workshop School Update for February 2013','','publish','open','open','','the-childrens-workshop-school-update-for-february-2013','','','2013-02-05 11:33:58','2013-02-05 16:33:58','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=781',0,'post','',0),(797,1,'2013-03-06 07:22:37','2013-03-06 12:22:37','In the meantime...buy your Tubby the Tuba raffle tickets this Thursday 7 March and Friday 8 March (drawing at Community Meeting on Friday)---$1 per chance/6 chances for $5--there will be 2 winners:\n\nWin  2 tickets or 3 tickets to see The Little Orchestra Society\'s production of the 1941 children\'s classic musical Tubby the Tuba narrated by Patti Smith on Saturday 16 March at 1pm at Lincoln Center!','March Update will be posted soon!','','publish','open','open','','march-update-will-be-posted-soon','','','2013-03-06 07:22:37','2013-03-06 12:22:37','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=797',0,'post','',0),(801,1,'2013-03-07 14:31:35','2013-03-07 19:31:35','<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Month of March 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">phone numbers:212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376</p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\" align=\"center\"><strong>Schoolapalooza, celebrating 20 years of CWS! New Date/Same Location:  Friday 26 April at Clemente Soto Velez Center on the corner of Rivington and Suffolk Streets.  Lisa Lisa confirmed to perform!!</strong>  Next Schoolapalooza planning meeting is Tuesday 12 March after drop-off at Continuum Coffee on Ave B.  Thanks to Ian, Rachel, Kim, Evan, Lori, Rodrigo, Cassie, Nancy, Sean, and Rina for their hard work thus far.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Keep those <strong>Schoolapalooza auction items</strong> coming in—<strong>the amazing donations thus far include:  a week at a house in Costa Rica, an American Girl doll, a two-hour New York harbor cruise on an Atlantic Yachting boat, one week in a fabulous 3-bedroom apartment in a medieval Tuscan village.  </strong>Thanks to Melissa, Francesca, Sayoko, Roxanne, Tiffany, Hope, Rachel, Kim, Nancy and Cassie for soliciting auction donations.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Our students are making a CD of the songs we sing at Community Meeting to sell at Schoolapalooza and beyond</strong>; everything from “We Shall Overcome” to “This Land is Your Land” to “We’re All a Family Under One Sky”—thanks to Tiffany, Elizabeth, Julie and our teachers, especially Gary.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Our students have raised almost $1900 for Hurricane Sandy relief</strong>, between all the class fundraisers, donated to Save the Children!  Thank you to our whole school community for coming together to help those in need.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe <strong>International Children’s Film Festival</strong>: fantastic films for children of all ages—March 1-21 at various locations—if you buy tickets online and select our school from the drop-down box, <strong>the festival will give $4 of every ticket to CWS</strong>.  <a href=\"http://www.gkids.com/\">http://www.gkids.com</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Raffle! TWO Winners!!:</strong>  <strong>Win 2 or 3 tickets to see Patti Smith narrate Tubby the Tuba at Lincoln Center on Sat 16 March at 1pm!!</strong>  Raffle tix will be sold in the lobby Fri 1 March, Thurs 7 March and Fri 8 March—drawing at Community Meeting on 8 March.  $1 per chance/$5 for 6 chances.  All proceeds go to benefit the many programs the PTA funds: everything from Turtle Bay Music to Bent on Learning yoga.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Clubs Showcase:  Patrizia’s Thursday Creative Movement/Improvisational Dance Club will perform at 4:15 in the lobby on Thurs 21 March</strong>.  All are welcome!  Come support the expressive dance talents of our students!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Class news:</strong> The 5<sup>th</sup> graders are enjoying learning to play <strong>golf</strong> at Chelsea Piers; the 2<sup>nd</sup> graders are getting <strong>swimming lessons</strong>, thanks to the NYC Dept of Parks and Recreation Swim for Life program; the 4<sup>th</sup> graders are looking forward to their upcoming <strong>farm trip</strong> and the 5<sup>th</sup> graders continue their fundraising for their <strong>Washington, DC trip</strong>.  The pre-k classes are beginning their butterfly unit with a visit to the <strong>Museum of Natural History</strong> and the ½ classes are finishing up their <strong>fairy tale books</strong> and looking forward to their Writing Celebrations.  The 3rd graders enjoyed their trip to the <strong>Museum of the American Indian</strong> and the kindergarteners celebrated the <strong>100<sup>th</sup> day of school</strong> by counting to 100 in many different ways.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Friday Bake Sale—now selling books too!</strong>  <strong>Please donate books (in good condition) and buy books—kids’ and adult books--$1 for hardcovers 50 cents for paperbacks.</strong>  Thank you to Melissa, Heather, Natalie, Roxanne, Paul, Sayoko and everyone who contributes to and buys from our Friday bake/book sales.  Thank you to <strong>Porto Rico</strong> for their donation of the coffee!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>David R’s film, “The Girl” will open in theaters March 8th, International Women’s Day, at the AMC Loews Theater on Third Ave and 11th Street and the Elinor Bunin Munroe Film Center at Lincoln Center.</strong> You can see a trailer and showtimes at: <a href=\"http://davidrikersthegirl.com/\">http://davidrikersthegirl.com</a>.  Congrats to David, Elizabeth, Laila and Maria!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Support local CWS family-owned/operated businesses</strong>:  mention CWS at <strong>Café Pick Me Up</strong> on Ave A and 9<sup>th</sup> Street, owned by Rossella, Pierluigi, Ciara and Ilaria –and Café Pick Me Up will donate 20% of your check to our school and enjoy the elegant Northern Italian cuisine at their other restaurant, <strong>Gnocco</strong>, on 10<sup>th</sup> Street across from Tompkins Square Park.  Enjoy the sangria and deliciously innovative Tusc-Mex fare at <strong>Matilda </strong>on 11<sup>th</sup> St near Ave C, owned by Maristella, Esteban and Matilida.  Buy organic and repurposed gifts at <strong>Sustainables NYC</strong> on Ave A between 8<sup>th</sup> and 9<sup>th</sup> St, owned by Valeria, Michael and Barbara.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>For families with middle/high schoolers:</strong>   <a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=9f79d936946147d297d1baf5c9fb1bdf&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.artsconnection.org\" target=\"_blank\">ArtsConnection</a>, a non-profit arts education program, offers discounts to cultural events all over the city for ages 13-18. Thanks to Rina for sharing this info with the CWS community:\n\n<a href=\"https://mail.qcc.cuny.edu/owa/redir.aspx?C=9f79d936946147d297d1baf5c9fb1bdf&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.high5tix.org\" target=\"_blank\">High 5: Tickets to the Arts</a>\n\n<strong>highfivetix.org</strong>\n\nAffordable tickets to NYC arts programs, exhibits and shows for teenagers 13 to 18 only and teens from anywhere in the world that are visiting NYC.  They can experience dance, music, theater and visual arts events all year round. Tickets to museums are only two for $5!!!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 4 March:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWeds 6 March-PTA Exec Board meeting 8:40am in library conference room\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFriday 8 March:  School Leadership Team meeting, 7:30am in Suma’s classroom\n\nTubby the Tuba raffle tix drawing at Community Meeting\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 11 March:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Tues 12 March—1/2 day—dismissal at 11:30 (no clubs!)—afternoon family conferences</strong>\n\n<strong>                        Schoolapalooza meeting at Continuum Coffee after drop-off</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Weds 13 March—no clubs-evening family conferences</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Week of 18 March:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Weds 20 March:  PTA meeting in cafeteria after drop-off</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThurs 21 March: Spring Photos! and  <strong>Clubs Showcase at 4:15 in the lobby:  The Thurs Creative Movement Improvisational Dance Club will perform!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Fri 22 March:  Crazy Hair Day!!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Saturday 23 March to Tues 2 April:  SPRING BREAK!!!  ENJOY!!!  SEE YOU WEDS 3 APRIL!!!</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Looking Forward!:</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSave the date and put aside gently worn clothes/toys for the rummage sale:  <strong>The Arts and Science Fair is Saturday 11 May, a fun day for the whole family</strong>—science and art projects, games, face painting, live music and great food. CWS alumni will run the Lemon Bottle Rocket booth and the Glop booth.  <strong>Judy will chair yet again (hugs to Judy for fourteen years of the Arts and Science Fair)!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe <strong>Book Fair to benefit our beautiful library will be in June</strong> at Barnes and Noble everywhere—just in time to buy Summer Reading books.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you have any items for this update, email Beth: bcounihan@qcc.cuny.edu\n\n&nbsp;\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>The Children’s Workshop School Update</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>For the Month of March 2013</strong></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org/\">http://www.childrensworkshopschool.org</a></p>\n<p align=\"center\">phone numbers:212-614-9531 or 347-675-9415 or 347-675-9376</p>\n<p align=\"center\">”We’re all a family under one sky!”</p>','The Children\'s Workshop School Update for March 2013','','publish','open','open','','801','','','2013-03-07 14:31:35','2013-03-07 19:31:35','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=801',0,'post','',0),(805,1,'2013-03-17 20:27:15','2013-03-18 00:27:15','Please take your time to fill out your <a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/Accountability/tools/survey/default.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">NYC School 2013 Parent SURVEY</span></a> that you have received at your Parent Teacher Conference. Please send in the 2013 Parent Survey before April 12. If you don\'t have the paper, you can also go online and take the survey. Please contact the school office if you do not have your Survey Access Code. This survey is very important for the next school year for our school.\n\nYou can take the survey here<a title=\"2013 Parent Survey\" href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/Accountability/tools/survey/default.htm\" target=\"_blank\">&gt;&gt;&gt;nycschoolsurvey.org</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/Accountability/tools/survey/default.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone\" title=\"school survey count\" src=\"http://schools.nyc.gov/WebServices/Imaging/SurveyCounter.ashx\" alt=\"\" width=\"206\" height=\"175\" /></a>','Your School, Your Voice','','publish','open','open','','your-school-your-voice','','','2013-03-17 20:27:15','2013-03-18 00:27:15','',0,'http://childrensworkshopschool.org/?p=805',0,'post','',0),(1742,1,'2014-12-24 11:20:52','2014-12-24 16:20:52','','PTA','','publish','open','open','','pta-3','','','2015-01-17 11:39:15','2015-01-17 16:39:15','',0,'http://cws.elab.io/pta-3/',35,'nav_men